80// Our MarginInfo state used when laying out block children.
81RenderBlockFlow::MarginInfo::MarginInfo(const RenderBlockFlow& block, LayoutUnit beforeBorderPadding, LayoutUnit afterBorderPadding)
82 : m_atBeforeSideOfBlock(true)
83 , m_atAfterSideOfBlock(false)
84 , m_hasMarginBeforeQuirk(false)
85 , m_hasMarginAfterQuirk(false)
86 , m_determinedMarginBeforeQuirk(false)
87 , m_discardMargin(false)
88{
89 const RenderStyle& blockStyle = block.style();
90 ASSERT(block.isRenderView() || block.parent());
91 m_canCollapseWithChildren = !block.createsNewFormattingContext() && !block.isRenderView();
92
93 m_canCollapseMarginBeforeWithChildren = m_canCollapseWithChildren && !beforeBorderPadding && blockStyle.marginBeforeCollapse() != MarginCollapse::Separate;
94
95 // If any height other than auto is specified in CSS, then we don't collapse our bottom
96 // margins with our children's margins. To do otherwise would be to risk odd visual
97 // effects when the children overflow out of the parent block and yet still collapse
98 // with it. We also don't collapse if we have any bottom border/padding.
99 m_canCollapseMarginAfterWithChildren = m_canCollapseWithChildren && !afterBorderPadding
100 && (blockStyle.logicalHeight().isAuto() && !blockStyle.logicalHeight().value()) && blockStyle.marginAfterCollapse() != MarginCollapse::Separate;
101
102 m_quirkContainer = block.isTableCell() || block.isBody();
103
104 m_discardMargin = m_canCollapseMarginBeforeWithChildren && block.mustDiscardMarginBefore();
105
106 m_positiveMargin = (m_canCollapseMarginBeforeWithChildren && !block.mustDiscardMarginBefore()) ? block.maxPositiveMarginBefore() : 0_lu;
107 m_negativeMargin = (m_canCollapseMarginBeforeWithChildren && !block.mustDiscardMarginBefore()) ? block.maxNegativeMarginBefore() : 0_lu;
108}

135void RenderBlockFlow::willBeDestroyed()
136{
137 if (!renderTreeBeingDestroyed()) {
138 if (firstRootBox()) {
139 // We can't wait for RenderBox::destroy to clear the selection,
140 // because by then we will have nuked the line boxes.
141 if (isSelectionBorder())
142 frame().selection().setNeedsSelectionUpdate();
143
144 // If we are an anonymous block, then our line boxes might have children
145 // that will outlast this block. In the non-anonymous block case those
146 // children will be destroyed by the time we return from this function.
147 if (isAnonymousBlock()) {
148 for (auto* box = firstRootBox(); box; box = box->nextRootBox()) {
149 while (auto childBox = box->firstChild())
150 childBox->removeFromParent();
151 }
152 }
153 } else if (parent())
154 parent()->dirtyLinesFromChangedChild(*this);
155 }
156
157 if (legacyLineLayout())
158 legacyLineLayout()->lineBoxes().deleteLineBoxes();
159
160 blockWillBeDestroyed();
161
162 // NOTE: This jumps down to RenderBox, bypassing RenderBlock since it would do duplicate work.
163 RenderBox::willBeDestroyed();
164}

171RenderBlockFlow* RenderBlockFlow::previousSiblingWithOverhangingFloats(bool& parentHasFloats) const
172{
173 // Attempt to locate a previous sibling with overhanging floats. We skip any elements that are
174 // out of flow (like floating/positioned elements), and we also skip over any objects that may have shifted
175 // to avoid floats.
176 parentHasFloats = false;
177 for (RenderObject* sibling = previousSibling(); sibling; sibling = sibling->previousSibling()) {
178 if (is<RenderBlockFlow>(*sibling)) {
179 auto& siblingBlock = downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*sibling);
180 if (!siblingBlock.avoidsFloats())
181 return &siblingBlock;
182 }
183 if (sibling->isFloating())
184 parentHasFloats = true;
185 }
186 return nullptr;
187}
188
189void RenderBlockFlow::rebuildFloatingObjectSetFromIntrudingFloats()
190{
191 if (m_floatingObjects)
192 m_floatingObjects->setHorizontalWritingMode(isHorizontalWritingMode());
193
194 HashSet<RenderBox*> oldIntrudingFloatSet;
195 if (!childrenInline() && m_floatingObjects) {
196 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_floatingObjects->set();
197 auto end = floatingObjectSet.end();
198 for (auto it = floatingObjectSet.begin(); it != end; ++it) {
199 FloatingObject* floatingObject = it->get();
200 if (!floatingObject->isDescendant())
201 oldIntrudingFloatSet.add(&floatingObject->renderer());
202 }
203 }
204
205 // Inline blocks are covered by the isReplaced() check in the avoidFloats method.
206 if (avoidsFloats() || isDocumentElementRenderer() || isRenderView() || isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned() || isTableCell()) {
207 if (m_floatingObjects)
208 m_floatingObjects->clear();
209 if (!oldIntrudingFloatSet.isEmpty())
210 markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout();
211 return;
212 }
213
214 RendererToFloatInfoMap floatMap;
215
216 if (m_floatingObjects) {
217 if (childrenInline())
218 m_floatingObjects->moveAllToFloatInfoMap(floatMap);
219 else
220 m_floatingObjects->clear();
221 }
222
223 // We should not process floats if the parent node is not a RenderBlock. Otherwise, we will add
224 // floats in an invalid context. This will cause a crash arising from a bad cast on the parent.
225 // See <rdar://problem/8049753>, where float property is applied on a text node in a SVG.
226 if (!is<RenderBlockFlow>(parent()))
227 return;
228
229 // First add in floats from the parent. Self-collapsing blocks let their parent track any floats that intrude into
230 // them (as opposed to floats they contain themselves) so check for those here too.
231 auto& parentBlock = downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*parent());
232 bool parentHasFloats = false;
233 RenderBlockFlow* previousBlock = previousSiblingWithOverhangingFloats(parentHasFloats);
234 LayoutUnit logicalTopOffset = logicalTop();
235 if (parentHasFloats || (parentBlock.lowestFloatLogicalBottom() > logicalTopOffset && previousBlock && previousBlock->isSelfCollapsingBlock()))
236 addIntrudingFloats(&parentBlock, &parentBlock, parentBlock.logicalLeftOffsetForContent(), logicalTopOffset);
237
238 LayoutUnit logicalLeftOffset;
239 if (previousBlock)
240 logicalTopOffset -= previousBlock->logicalTop();
241 else {
242 previousBlock = &parentBlock;
243 logicalLeftOffset += parentBlock.logicalLeftOffsetForContent();
244 }
245
246 // Add overhanging floats from the previous RenderBlock, but only if it has a float that intrudes into our space.
247 if (previousBlock->m_floatingObjects && previousBlock->lowestFloatLogicalBottom() > logicalTopOffset)
248 addIntrudingFloats(previousBlock, &parentBlock, logicalLeftOffset, logicalTopOffset);
249
250 if (childrenInline()) {
251 LayoutUnit changeLogicalTop = LayoutUnit::max();
252 LayoutUnit changeLogicalBottom = LayoutUnit::min();
253 if (m_floatingObjects) {
254 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_floatingObjects->set();
255 auto end = floatingObjectSet.end();
256 for (auto it = floatingObjectSet.begin(); it != end; ++it) {
257 const auto& floatingObject = *it->get();
258 std::unique_ptr<FloatingObject> oldFloatingObject = floatMap.take(&floatingObject.renderer());
259 LayoutUnit logicalBottom = logicalBottomForFloat(floatingObject);
260 if (oldFloatingObject) {
261 LayoutUnit oldLogicalBottom = logicalBottomForFloat(*oldFloatingObject);
262 if (logicalWidthForFloat(floatingObject) != logicalWidthForFloat(*oldFloatingObject) || logicalLeftForFloat(floatingObject) != logicalLeftForFloat(*oldFloatingObject)) {
263 changeLogicalTop = 0;
264 changeLogicalBottom = std::max(changeLogicalBottom, std::max(logicalBottom, oldLogicalBottom));
265 } else {
266 if (logicalBottom != oldLogicalBottom) {
267 changeLogicalTop = std::min(changeLogicalTop, std::min(logicalBottom, oldLogicalBottom));
268 changeLogicalBottom = std::max(changeLogicalBottom, std::max(logicalBottom, oldLogicalBottom));
269 }
270 LayoutUnit logicalTop = logicalTopForFloat(floatingObject);
271 LayoutUnit oldLogicalTop = logicalTopForFloat(*oldFloatingObject);
272 if (logicalTop != oldLogicalTop) {
273 changeLogicalTop = std::min(changeLogicalTop, std::min(logicalTop, oldLogicalTop));
274 changeLogicalBottom = std::max(changeLogicalBottom, std::max(logicalTop, oldLogicalTop));
275 }
276 }
277
278 if (oldFloatingObject->originatingLine() && !selfNeedsLayout()) {
279 ASSERT(&oldFloatingObject->originatingLine()->renderer() == this);
280 oldFloatingObject->originatingLine()->markDirty();
281 }
282 } else {
283 changeLogicalTop = 0;
284 changeLogicalBottom = std::max(changeLogicalBottom, logicalBottom);
285 }
286 }
287 }
288
289 auto end = floatMap.end();
290 for (auto it = floatMap.begin(); it != end; ++it) {
291 const auto& floatingObject = *it->value.get();
292 if (!floatingObject.isDescendant()) {
293 changeLogicalTop = 0;
294 changeLogicalBottom = std::max(changeLogicalBottom, logicalBottomForFloat(floatingObject));
295 }
296 }
297
298 markLinesDirtyInBlockRange(changeLogicalTop, changeLogicalBottom);
299 } else if (!oldIntrudingFloatSet.isEmpty()) {
300 // If there are previously intruding floats that no longer intrude, then children with floats
301 // should also get layout because they might need their floating object lists cleared.
302 if (m_floatingObjects->set().size() < oldIntrudingFloatSet.size())
303 markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout();
304 else {
305 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_floatingObjects->set();
306 auto end = floatingObjectSet.end();
307 for (auto it = floatingObjectSet.begin(); it != end && !oldIntrudingFloatSet.isEmpty(); ++it)
308 oldIntrudingFloatSet.remove(&(*it)->renderer());
309 if (!oldIntrudingFloatSet.isEmpty())
310 markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout();
311 }
312 }
313}

315void RenderBlockFlow::adjustIntrinsicLogicalWidthsForColumns(LayoutUnit& minLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit& maxLogicalWidth) const
316{
317 if (!style().hasAutoColumnCount() || !style().hasAutoColumnWidth()) {
318 // The min/max intrinsic widths calculated really tell how much space elements need when
319 // laid out inside the columns. In order to eventually end up with the desired column width,
320 // we need to convert them to values pertaining to the multicol container.
321 int columnCount = style().hasAutoColumnCount() ? 1 : style().columnCount();
322 LayoutUnit columnWidth;
323 LayoutUnit colGap = columnGap();
324 LayoutUnit gapExtra = (columnCount - 1) * colGap;
325 if (style().hasAutoColumnWidth())
326 minLogicalWidth = minLogicalWidth * columnCount + gapExtra;
327 else {
328 columnWidth = style().columnWidth();
329 minLogicalWidth = std::min(minLogicalWidth, columnWidth);
330 }
331 // FIXME: If column-count is auto here, we should resolve it to calculate the maximum
332 // intrinsic width, instead of pretending that it's 1. The only way to do that is by
333 // performing a layout pass, but this is not an appropriate time or place for layout. The
334 // good news is that if height is unconstrained and there are no explicit breaks, the
335 // resolved column-count really should be 1.
336 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(maxLogicalWidth, columnWidth) * columnCount + gapExtra;
337 }
338}
339
340void RenderBlockFlow::computeIntrinsicLogicalWidths(LayoutUnit& minLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit& maxLogicalWidth) const
341{
342 if (!shouldApplySizeContainment(*this)) {
343 if (childrenInline())
344 computeInlinePreferredLogicalWidths(minLogicalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
345 else
346 computeBlockPreferredLogicalWidths(minLogicalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
347 }
348
349 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(minLogicalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
350
351 adjustIntrinsicLogicalWidthsForColumns(minLogicalWidth, maxLogicalWidth);
352
353 if (!style().autoWrap() && childrenInline()) {
354 // A horizontal marquee with inline children has no minimum width.
355 auto* scrollableArea = layer() ? layer()->scrollableArea() : nullptr;
356 if (scrollableArea && scrollableArea->marquee() && scrollableArea->marquee()->isHorizontal())
357 minLogicalWidth = 0;
358 }
359
360 if (is<RenderTableCell>(*this)) {
361 Length tableCellWidth = downcast<RenderTableCell>(*this).styleOrColLogicalWidth();
362 if (tableCellWidth.isFixed() && tableCellWidth.value() > 0)
363 maxLogicalWidth = std::max(minLogicalWidth, adjustContentBoxLogicalWidthForBoxSizing(tableCellWidth));
364 }
365
366 int scrollbarWidth = intrinsicScrollbarLogicalWidth();
367 maxLogicalWidth += scrollbarWidth;
368 minLogicalWidth += scrollbarWidth;
369}
370
371bool RenderBlockFlow::recomputeLogicalWidthAndColumnWidth()
372{
373 bool changed = recomputeLogicalWidth();
374
375 LayoutUnit oldColumnWidth = computedColumnWidth();
376 computeColumnCountAndWidth();
377
378 return changed || oldColumnWidth != computedColumnWidth();
379}

381LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::columnGap() const
382{
383 if (style().columnGap().isNormal())
384 return style().fontDescription().computedPixelSize(); // "1em" is recommended as the normal gap setting. Matches <p> margins.
385 return valueForLength(style().columnGap().length(), availableLogicalWidth());
386}

388void RenderBlockFlow::computeColumnCountAndWidth()
389{
390 // Calculate our column width and column count.
391 // FIXME: Can overflow on fast/block/float/float-not-removed-from-next-sibling4.html, see https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=68744
392 unsigned desiredColumnCount = 1;
393 LayoutUnit desiredColumnWidth = contentLogicalWidth();
394
395 // For now, we don't support multi-column layouts when printing, since we have to do a lot of work for proper pagination.
396 if (document().paginated() || (style().hasAutoColumnCount() && style().hasAutoColumnWidth()) || !style().hasInlineColumnAxis()) {
397 setComputedColumnCountAndWidth(desiredColumnCount, desiredColumnWidth);
398 return;
399 }
400
401 LayoutUnit availWidth = desiredColumnWidth;
402 LayoutUnit colGap = columnGap();
403 LayoutUnit colWidth = std::max(1_lu, LayoutUnit(style().columnWidth()));
404 unsigned colCount = std::max<unsigned>(1, style().columnCount());
405
406 if (style().hasAutoColumnWidth() && !style().hasAutoColumnCount()) {
407 desiredColumnCount = colCount;
408 desiredColumnWidth = std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, (availWidth - ((desiredColumnCount - 1) * colGap)) / desiredColumnCount);
409 } else if (!style().hasAutoColumnWidth() && style().hasAutoColumnCount()) {
410 desiredColumnCount = std::max<unsigned>(1, ((availWidth + colGap) / (colWidth + colGap)).toUnsigned());
411 desiredColumnWidth = ((availWidth + colGap) / desiredColumnCount) - colGap;
412 } else {
413 desiredColumnCount = std::max<unsigned>(std::min(colCount, ((availWidth + colGap) / (colWidth + colGap)).toUnsigned()), 1);
414 desiredColumnWidth = ((availWidth + colGap) / desiredColumnCount) - colGap;
415 }
416 setComputedColumnCountAndWidth(desiredColumnCount, desiredColumnWidth);
417}
418
419bool RenderBlockFlow::willCreateColumns(std::optional<unsigned> desiredColumnCount) const
420{
421 // The following types are not supposed to create multicol context.
422 if (isFileUploadControl() || isTextControl() || isListBox())
423 return false;
424 if (isRenderSVGBlock() || isRubyRun())
425 return false;
426#if ENABLE(MATHML)
427 if (isRenderMathMLBlock())
428 return false;
429#endif // ENABLE(MATHML)
430
431 if (!firstChild())
432 return false;
433
434 if (style().styleType() != PseudoId::None)
435 return false;
436
437 // If overflow-y is set to paged-x or paged-y on the body or html element, we'll handle the paginating in the RenderView instead.
438 if ((style().overflowY() == Overflow::PagedX || style().overflowY() == Overflow::PagedY) && !(isDocumentElementRenderer() || isBody()))
439 return true;
440
441 if (!style().specifiesColumns())
442 return false;
443
444 // column-axis with opposite writing direction initiates MultiColumnFlow.
445 if (!style().hasInlineColumnAxis())
446 return true;
447
448 // Non-auto column-width always initiates MultiColumnFlow.
449 if (!style().hasAutoColumnWidth())
450 return true;
451
452 if (desiredColumnCount)
453 return desiredColumnCount.value() > 1;
454
455 // column-count > 1 always initiates MultiColumnFlow.
456 if (!style().hasAutoColumnCount())
457 return style().columnCount() > 1;
458
459 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
460 return false;
461}

473void RenderBlockFlow::layoutBlock(bool relayoutChildren, LayoutUnit pageLogicalHeight)
474{
475 ASSERT(needsLayout());
476
477 if (!relayoutChildren && simplifiedLayout())
478 return;
479
480 LayoutRepainter repainter(*this, checkForRepaintDuringLayout());
481
482 if (recomputeLogicalWidthAndColumnWidth())
483 relayoutChildren = true;
484
485 rebuildFloatingObjectSetFromIntrudingFloats();
486
487 LayoutUnit previousHeight = logicalHeight();
488 // FIXME: should this start out as borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight() + scrollbarLogicalHeight(),
489 // for consistency with other render classes?
490 resetLogicalHeightBeforeLayoutIfNeeded();
491
492 bool pageLogicalHeightChanged = false;
493 checkForPaginationLogicalHeightChange(relayoutChildren, pageLogicalHeight, pageLogicalHeightChanged);
494
495 LayoutUnit repaintLogicalTop;
496 LayoutUnit repaintLogicalBottom;
497 LayoutUnit maxFloatLogicalBottom;
498 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
499 {
500 LayoutStateMaintainer statePusher(*this, locationOffset(), hasTransform() || hasReflection() || styleToUse.isFlippedBlocksWritingMode(), pageLogicalHeight, pageLogicalHeightChanged);
501
502 preparePaginationBeforeBlockLayout(relayoutChildren);
503
504 // We use four values, maxTopPos, maxTopNeg, maxBottomPos, and maxBottomNeg, to track
505 // our current maximal positive and negative margins. These values are used when we
506 // are collapsed with adjacent blocks, so for example, if you have block A and B
507 // collapsing together, then you'd take the maximal positive margin from both A and B
508 // and subtract it from the maximal negative margin from both A and B to get the
509 // true collapsed margin. This algorithm is recursive, so when we finish layout()
510 // our block knows its current maximal positive/negative values.
511 //
512 // Start out by setting our margin values to our current margins. Table cells have
513 // no margins, so we don't fill in the values for table cells.
514 bool isCell = isTableCell();
515 if (!isCell) {
516 initMaxMarginValues();
517
518 setHasMarginBeforeQuirk(styleToUse.hasMarginBeforeQuirk());
519 setHasMarginAfterQuirk(styleToUse.hasMarginAfterQuirk());
520 setPaginationStrut(0);
521 }
522 if (!firstChild() && !isAnonymousBlock())
523 setChildrenInline(true);
524 if (childrenInline())
525 layoutInlineChildren(relayoutChildren, repaintLogicalTop, repaintLogicalBottom);
526 else
527 layoutBlockChildren(relayoutChildren, maxFloatLogicalBottom);
528 }
529
530 // Expand our intrinsic height to encompass floats.
531 LayoutUnit toAdd = borderAndPaddingAfter() + scrollbarLogicalHeight();
532 if (lowestFloatLogicalBottom() > (logicalHeight() - toAdd) && createsNewFormattingContext())
533 setLogicalHeight(lowestFloatLogicalBottom() + toAdd);
534 if (relayoutForPagination() || relayoutToAvoidWidows()) {
535 ASSERT(!shouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow());
536 return;
537 }
538
539 // Calculate our new height.
540 LayoutUnit oldHeight = logicalHeight();
541 LayoutUnit oldClientAfterEdge = clientLogicalBottom();
542
543 // Before updating the final size of the flow thread make sure a forced break is applied after the content.
544 // This ensures the size information is correctly computed for the last auto-height fragment receiving content.
545 if (is<RenderFragmentedFlow>(*this))
546 downcast<RenderFragmentedFlow>(*this).applyBreakAfterContent(oldClientAfterEdge);
547
548 updateLogicalHeight();
549 LayoutUnit newHeight = logicalHeight();
550 {
551 // FIXME: This could be removed once relayoutForPagination()/relayoutToAvoidWidows() either stop recursing or we manage to
552 // re-order them.
553 LayoutStateMaintainer statePusher(*this, locationOffset(), hasTransform() || hasReflection() || styleToUse.isFlippedBlocksWritingMode(), pageLogicalHeight, pageLogicalHeightChanged);
554
555 if (oldHeight != newHeight) {
556 if (oldHeight > newHeight && maxFloatLogicalBottom > newHeight && !childrenInline()) {
557 // One of our children's floats may have become an overhanging float for us. We need to look for it.
558 for (auto& blockFlow : childrenOfType<RenderBlockFlow>(*this)) {
559 if (blockFlow.isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
560 continue;
561 if (blockFlow.lowestFloatLogicalBottom() + blockFlow.logicalTop() > newHeight)
562 addOverhangingFloats(blockFlow, false);
563 }
564 }
565 }
566
567 bool heightChanged = (previousHeight != newHeight);
568 if (heightChanged)
569 relayoutChildren = true;
570 layoutPositionedObjects(relayoutChildren || isDocumentElementRenderer());
571 }
572 // Add overflow from children (unless we're multi-column, since in that case all our child overflow is clipped anyway).
573 computeOverflow(oldClientAfterEdge);
574
575 fitBorderToLinesIfNeeded();
576
577 auto* state = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState();
578 if (state && state->pageLogicalHeight())
579 setPageLogicalOffset(state->pageLogicalOffset(this, logicalTop()));
580
581 updateLayerTransform();
582
583 // Update our scroll information if we're overflow:auto/scroll/hidden now that we know if
584 // we overflow or not.
585 updateScrollInfoAfterLayout();
586
587 // FIXME: This repaint logic should be moved into a separate helper function!
588 // Repaint with our new bounds if they are different from our old bounds.
589 bool didFullRepaint = repainter.repaintAfterLayout();
590 if (!didFullRepaint && repaintLogicalTop != repaintLogicalBottom && (styleToUse.visibility() == Visibility::Visible || enclosingLayer()->hasVisibleContent())) {
591 // FIXME: We could tighten up the left and right invalidation points if we let layoutInlineChildren fill them in based off the particular lines
592 // it had to lay out. We wouldn't need the hasOverflowClip() hack in that case either.
593 LayoutUnit repaintLogicalLeft = logicalLeftVisualOverflow();
594 LayoutUnit repaintLogicalRight = logicalRightVisualOverflow();
595 if (hasOverflowClip()) {
596 // If we have clipped overflow, we should use layout overflow as well, since visual overflow from lines didn't propagate to our block's overflow.
597 // Note the old code did this as well but even for overflow:visible. The addition of hasOverflowClip() at least tightens up the hack a bit.
598 // layoutInlineChildren should be patched to compute the entire repaint rect.
599 repaintLogicalLeft = std::min(repaintLogicalLeft, logicalLeftLayoutOverflow());
600 repaintLogicalRight = std::max(repaintLogicalRight, logicalRightLayoutOverflow());
601 }
602
603 LayoutRect repaintRect;
604 if (isHorizontalWritingMode())
605 repaintRect = LayoutRect(repaintLogicalLeft, repaintLogicalTop, repaintLogicalRight - repaintLogicalLeft, repaintLogicalBottom - repaintLogicalTop);
606 else
607 repaintRect = LayoutRect(repaintLogicalTop, repaintLogicalLeft, repaintLogicalBottom - repaintLogicalTop, repaintLogicalRight - repaintLogicalLeft);
608
609 if (hasOverflowClip()) {
610 // Adjust repaint rect for scroll offset
611 repaintRect.moveBy(-scrollPosition());
612
613 // Don't allow this rect to spill out of our overflow box.
614 repaintRect.intersect(LayoutRect(LayoutPoint(), size()));
615 }
616
617 // Make sure the rect is still non-empty after intersecting for overflow above
618 if (!repaintRect.isEmpty()) {
619 repaintRectangle(repaintRect); // We need to do a partial repaint of our content.
620 if (hasReflection())
621 repaintRectangle(reflectedRect(repaintRect));
622 }
623 }
624
625 clearNeedsLayout();
626}
627
628void RenderBlockFlow::layoutBlockChildren(bool relayoutChildren, LayoutUnit& maxFloatLogicalBottom)
629{
630 dirtyForLayoutFromPercentageHeightDescendants();
631
632 LayoutUnit beforeEdge = borderAndPaddingBefore();
633 LayoutUnit afterEdge = borderAndPaddingAfter() + scrollbarLogicalHeight();
634
635 setLogicalHeight(beforeEdge);
636
637 // Lay out our hypothetical grid line as though it occurs at the top of the block.
638 if (view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->lineGrid() == this)
639 layoutLineGridBox();
640
641 // The margin struct caches all our current margin collapsing state.
642 MarginInfo marginInfo(*this, beforeEdge, afterEdge);
643
644 // Fieldsets need to find their legend and position it inside the border of the object.
645 // The legend then gets skipped during normal layout. The same is true for ruby text.
646 // It doesn't get included in the normal layout process but is instead skipped.
647 layoutExcludedChildren(relayoutChildren);
648
649 LayoutUnit previousFloatLogicalBottom;
650 maxFloatLogicalBottom = 0;
651
652 RenderBox* next = firstChildBox();
653
654 while (next) {
655 RenderBox& child = *next;
656 next = child.nextSiblingBox();
657
658 if (child.isExcludedFromNormalLayout())
659 continue; // Skip this child, since it will be positioned by the specialized subclass (fieldsets and ruby runs).
660
661 updateBlockChildDirtyBitsBeforeLayout(relayoutChildren, child);
662
663 if (child.isOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
664 child.containingBlock()->insertPositionedObject(child);
665 adjustPositionedBlock(child, marginInfo);
666 continue;
667 }
668 if (child.isFloating()) {
669 insertFloatingObject(child);
670 adjustFloatingBlock(marginInfo);
671 continue;
672 }
673
674 // Lay out the child.
675 layoutBlockChild(child, marginInfo, previousFloatLogicalBottom, maxFloatLogicalBottom);
676 }
677
678 // Now do the handling of the bottom of the block, adding in our bottom border/padding and
679 // determining the correct collapsed bottom margin information.
680 handleAfterSideOfBlock(beforeEdge, afterEdge, marginInfo);
681}
682
683void RenderBlockFlow::layoutInlineChildren(bool relayoutChildren, LayoutUnit& repaintLogicalTop, LayoutUnit& repaintLogicalBottom)
684{
685 auto computeLineLayoutPath = [&] {
686#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
687 if (LayoutIntegration::LineLayout::canUseFor(*this))
688 return ModernPath;
689#endif
690 return LineBoxesPath;
691 };
692
693 if (lineLayoutPath() == UndeterminedPath)
694 setLineLayoutPath(computeLineLayoutPath());
695
696#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
697 if (lineLayoutPath() == ModernPath) {
698 layoutModernLines(relayoutChildren, repaintLogicalTop, repaintLogicalBottom);
699 return;
700 }
701#endif
702
703 if (!legacyLineLayout())
704 m_lineLayout = makeUnique<LegacyLineLayout>(*this);
705
706 legacyLineLayout()->layoutLineBoxes(relayoutChildren, repaintLogicalTop, repaintLogicalBottom);
707}
708
709void RenderBlockFlow::layoutBlockChild(RenderBox& child, MarginInfo& marginInfo, LayoutUnit& previousFloatLogicalBottom, LayoutUnit& maxFloatLogicalBottom)
710{
711 LayoutUnit oldPosMarginBefore = maxPositiveMarginBefore();
712 LayoutUnit oldNegMarginBefore = maxNegativeMarginBefore();
713
714 // The child is a normal flow object. Compute the margins we will use for collapsing now.
715 child.computeAndSetBlockDirectionMargins(*this);
716
717 // Try to guess our correct logical top position. In most cases this guess will
718 // be correct. Only if we're wrong (when we compute the real logical top position)
719 // will we have to potentially relayout.
720 LayoutUnit estimateWithoutPagination;
721 LayoutUnit logicalTopEstimate = estimateLogicalTopPosition(child, marginInfo, estimateWithoutPagination);
722
723 // Cache our old rect so that we can dirty the proper repaint rects if the child moves.
724 LayoutRect oldRect = child.frameRect();
725 LayoutUnit oldLogicalTop = logicalTopForChild(child);
726
727#if ASSERT_ENABLED
728 LayoutSize oldLayoutDelta = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutDelta();
729#endif
730 // Position the child as though it didn't collapse with the top.
731 setLogicalTopForChild(child, logicalTopEstimate, ApplyLayoutDelta);
732 estimateFragmentRangeForBoxChild(child);
733
734 RenderBlockFlow* childBlockFlow = is<RenderBlockFlow>(child) ? &downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(child) : nullptr;
735 bool markDescendantsWithFloats = false;
736 if (logicalTopEstimate != oldLogicalTop && !child.avoidsFloats() && childBlockFlow && childBlockFlow->containsFloats())
737 markDescendantsWithFloats = true;
738 else if (UNLIKELY(logicalTopEstimate.mightBeSaturated()))
739 // logicalTopEstimate, returned by estimateLogicalTopPosition, might be saturated for
740 // very large elements. If it does the comparison with oldLogicalTop might yield a
741 // false negative as adding and removing margins, borders etc from a saturated number
742 // might yield incorrect results. If this is the case always mark for layout.
743 markDescendantsWithFloats = true;
744 else if (!child.avoidsFloats() || child.shrinkToAvoidFloats()) {
745 // If an element might be affected by the presence of floats, then always mark it for
746 // layout.
747 LayoutUnit fb = std::max(previousFloatLogicalBottom, lowestFloatLogicalBottom());
748 if (fb > logicalTopEstimate)
749 markDescendantsWithFloats = true;
750 }
751
752 if (childBlockFlow) {
753 if (markDescendantsWithFloats)
754 childBlockFlow->markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout();
755 if (!child.isWritingModeRoot())
756 previousFloatLogicalBottom = std::max(previousFloatLogicalBottom, oldLogicalTop + childBlockFlow->lowestFloatLogicalBottom());
757 }
758
759 child.markForPaginationRelayoutIfNeeded();
760
761 bool childHadLayout = child.everHadLayout();
762 bool childNeededLayout = child.needsLayout();
763 if (childNeededLayout)
764 child.layout();
765
766 // Cache if we are at the top of the block right now.
767 bool atBeforeSideOfBlock = marginInfo.atBeforeSideOfBlock();
768
769 // Now determine the correct ypos based off examination of collapsing margin
770 // values.
771 LayoutUnit logicalTopBeforeClear = collapseMargins(child, marginInfo);
772
773 // Now check for clear.
774 LayoutUnit logicalTopAfterClear = clearFloatsIfNeeded(child, marginInfo, oldPosMarginBefore, oldNegMarginBefore, logicalTopBeforeClear);
775
776 bool paginated = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->isPaginated();
777 if (paginated)
778 logicalTopAfterClear = adjustBlockChildForPagination(logicalTopAfterClear, estimateWithoutPagination, child, atBeforeSideOfBlock && logicalTopBeforeClear == logicalTopAfterClear);
779
780 setLogicalTopForChild(child, logicalTopAfterClear, ApplyLayoutDelta);
781
782 // Now we have a final top position. See if it really does end up being different from our estimate.
783 // clearFloatsIfNeeded can also mark the child as needing a layout even though we didn't move. This happens
784 // when collapseMargins dynamically adds overhanging floats because of a child with negative margins.
785 if (logicalTopAfterClear != logicalTopEstimate || child.needsLayout() || (paginated && childBlockFlow && childBlockFlow->shouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow())) {
786 if (child.shrinkToAvoidFloats()) {
787 // The child's width depends on the line width. When the child shifts to clear an item, its width can
788 // change (because it has more available line width). So mark the item as dirty.
789 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
790 }
791
792 if (childBlockFlow) {
793 if (!child.avoidsFloats() && childBlockFlow->containsFloats())
794 childBlockFlow->markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout();
795 child.markForPaginationRelayoutIfNeeded();
796 }
797 }
798
799 if (updateFragmentRangeForBoxChild(child))
800 child.setNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
801
802 // In case our guess was wrong, relayout the child.
803 child.layoutIfNeeded();
804
805 // We are no longer at the top of the block if we encounter a non-empty child.
806 // This has to be done after checking for clear, so that margins can be reset if a clear occurred.
807 if (marginInfo.atBeforeSideOfBlock() && !child.isSelfCollapsingBlock())
808 marginInfo.setAtBeforeSideOfBlock(false);
809
810 // Now place the child in the correct left position
811 determineLogicalLeftPositionForChild(child, ApplyLayoutDelta);
812
813 // Update our height now that the child has been placed in the correct position.
814 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + logicalHeightForChildForFragmentation(child));
815 if (mustSeparateMarginAfterForChild(child)) {
816 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + marginAfterForChild(child));
817 marginInfo.clearMargin();
818 }
819 // If the child has overhanging floats that intrude into following siblings (or possibly out
820 // of this block), then the parent gets notified of the floats now.
821 if (childBlockFlow && childBlockFlow->containsFloats())
822 maxFloatLogicalBottom = std::max(maxFloatLogicalBottom, addOverhangingFloats(*childBlockFlow, !childNeededLayout));
823
824 LayoutSize childOffset = child.location() - oldRect.location();
825 if (childOffset.width() || childOffset.height()) {
826 view().frameView().layoutContext().addLayoutDelta(childOffset);
827
828 // If the child moved, we have to repaint it as well as any floating/positioned
829 // descendants. An exception is if we need a layout. In this case, we know we're going to
830 // repaint ourselves (and the child) anyway.
831 if (childHadLayout && !selfNeedsLayout() && child.checkForRepaintDuringLayout())
832 child.repaintDuringLayoutIfMoved(oldRect);
833 }
834
835 if (!childHadLayout && child.checkForRepaintDuringLayout()) {
836 child.repaint();
837 child.repaintOverhangingFloats(true);
838 }
839
840 if (paginated) {
841 if (RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow())
842 fragmentedFlow->fragmentedFlowDescendantBoxLaidOut(&child);
843 // Check for an after page/column break.
844 LayoutUnit newHeight = applyAfterBreak(child, logicalHeight(), marginInfo);
845 if (newHeight != height())
846 setLogicalHeight(newHeight);
847 }
848
849 ASSERT(view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutDeltaMatches(oldLayoutDelta));
850}
851
852void RenderBlockFlow::adjustPositionedBlock(RenderBox& child, const MarginInfo& marginInfo)
853{
854 bool isHorizontal = isHorizontalWritingMode();
855 bool hasStaticBlockPosition = child.style().hasStaticBlockPosition(isHorizontal);
856
857 LayoutUnit logicalTop = logicalHeight();
858 updateStaticInlinePositionForChild(child, logicalTop, DoNotIndentText);
859
860 if (!marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginBefore()) {
861 // Positioned blocks don't collapse margins, so add the margin provided by
862 // the container now. The child's own margin is added later when calculating its logical top.
863 LayoutUnit collapsedBeforePos = marginInfo.positiveMargin();
864 LayoutUnit collapsedBeforeNeg = marginInfo.negativeMargin();
865 logicalTop += collapsedBeforePos - collapsedBeforeNeg;
866 }
867
868 RenderLayer* childLayer = child.layer();
869 if (childLayer->staticBlockPosition() != logicalTop) {
870 childLayer->setStaticBlockPosition(logicalTop);
871 if (hasStaticBlockPosition)
872 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
873 }
874}
875
876LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::marginOffsetForSelfCollapsingBlock()
877{
878 ASSERT(isSelfCollapsingBlock());
879 RenderBlockFlow* parentBlock = downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(parent());
880 if (parentBlock && RenderStyle::usedClear(*this) != UsedClear::None && parentBlock->getClearDelta(*this, logicalHeight()))
881 return marginValuesForChild(*this).positiveMarginBefore();
882 return 0_lu;
883}
884
885void RenderBlockFlow::determineLogicalLeftPositionForChild(RenderBox& child, ApplyLayoutDeltaMode applyDelta)
886{
887 LayoutUnit startPosition = borderStart() + paddingStart();
888 if (shouldPlaceVerticalScrollbarOnLeft() && isHorizontalWritingMode())
889 startPosition += (style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? 1 : -1) * verticalScrollbarWidth();
890 LayoutUnit totalAvailableLogicalWidth = borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth() + availableLogicalWidth();
891
892 // Add in our start margin.
893 LayoutUnit childMarginStart = marginStartForChild(child);
894 LayoutUnit newPosition = startPosition + childMarginStart;
895
896 // Some objects (e.g., tables, horizontal rules, overflow:auto blocks) avoid floats. They need
897 // to shift over as necessary to dodge any floats that might get in the way.
898 if (child.avoidsFloats() && containsFloats())
899 newPosition += computeStartPositionDeltaForChildAvoidingFloats(child, marginStartForChild(child));
900
901 setLogicalLeftForChild(child, style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? newPosition : totalAvailableLogicalWidth - newPosition - logicalWidthForChild(child), applyDelta);
902}
903
904void RenderBlockFlow::adjustFloatingBlock(const MarginInfo& marginInfo)
905{
906 // The float should be positioned taking into account the bottom margin
907 // of the previous flow. We add that margin into the height, get the
908 // float positioned properly, and then subtract the margin out of the
909 // height again. In the case of self-collapsing blocks, we always just
910 // use the top margins, since the self-collapsing block collapsed its
911 // own bottom margin into its top margin.
912 //
913 // Note also that the previous flow may collapse its margin into the top of
914 // our block. If this is the case, then we do not add the margin in to our
915 // height when computing the position of the float. This condition can be tested
916 // for by simply calling canCollapseWithMarginBefore. See
917 // http://www.hixie.ch/tests/adhoc/css/box/block/margin-collapse/046.html for
918 // an example of this scenario.
919 LayoutUnit marginOffset = marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginBefore() ? 0_lu : marginInfo.margin();
920 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + marginOffset);
921 positionNewFloats();
922 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() - marginOffset);
923}
924
925void RenderBlockFlow::updateStaticInlinePositionForChild(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit logicalTop, IndentTextOrNot shouldIndentText)
926{
927 if (child.style().isOriginalDisplayInlineType())
928 setStaticInlinePositionForChild(child, logicalTop, startAlignedOffsetForLine(logicalTop, shouldIndentText));
929 else
930 setStaticInlinePositionForChild(child, logicalTop, startOffsetForContent(logicalTop));
931}
932
933void RenderBlockFlow::setStaticInlinePositionForChild(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit blockOffset, LayoutUnit inlinePosition)
934{
935 if (enclosingFragmentedFlow()) {
936 // Shift the inline position to exclude the fragment offset.
937 inlinePosition += startOffsetForContent() - startOffsetForContent(blockOffset);
938 }
939 child.layer()->setStaticInlinePosition(inlinePosition);
940}
941
942LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::startAlignedOffsetForLine(LayoutUnit position, IndentTextOrNot shouldIndentText)
943{
944 TextAlignMode textAlign = style().textAlign();
945 bool shouldApplyIndentText = false;
946 switch (textAlign) {
947 case TextAlignMode::Left:
948 case TextAlignMode::WebKitLeft:
949 shouldApplyIndentText = style().isLeftToRightDirection();
950 break;
951 case TextAlignMode::Right:
952 case TextAlignMode::WebKitRight:
953 shouldApplyIndentText = !style().isLeftToRightDirection();
954 break;
955 case TextAlignMode::Start:
956 shouldApplyIndentText = true;
957 break;
958 default:
959 shouldApplyIndentText = false;
960 }
961 // <rdar://problem/15427571>
962 // https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=124522
963 // This quirk is for legacy content that doesn't work properly with the center positioning scheme
964 // being honored (e.g., epubs).
965 if (shouldApplyIndentText || settings().useLegacyTextAlignPositionedElementBehavior()) // FIXME: Handle TextAlignMode::End here
966 return startOffsetForLine(position, shouldIndentText);
967
968 // updateLogicalWidthForAlignment() handles the direction of the block so no need to consider it here
969 float totalLogicalWidth = 0;
970 float logicalLeft = logicalLeftOffsetForLine(logicalHeight(), DoNotIndentText);
971 float availableLogicalWidth = logicalRightOffsetForLine(logicalHeight(), DoNotIndentText) - logicalLeft;
972
973 LegacyLineLayout::updateLogicalWidthForAlignment(*this, textAlign, nullptr, nullptr, logicalLeft, totalLogicalWidth, availableLogicalWidth, 0);
974
975 if (!style().isLeftToRightDirection())
976 return LayoutUnit(logicalWidth() - logicalLeft);
977
978 return LayoutUnit(logicalLeft);
979}
980
981RenderBlockFlow::MarginValues RenderBlockFlow::marginValuesForChild(RenderBox& child) const
982{
983 LayoutUnit childBeforePositive;
984 LayoutUnit childBeforeNegative;
985 LayoutUnit childAfterPositive;
986 LayoutUnit childAfterNegative;
987
988 LayoutUnit beforeMargin;
989 LayoutUnit afterMargin;
990
991 RenderBlockFlow* childRenderBlock = is<RenderBlockFlow>(child) ? &downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(child) : nullptr;
992
993 // If the child has the same directionality as we do, then we can just return its
994 // margins in the same direction.
995 if (!child.isWritingModeRoot()) {
996 if (childRenderBlock) {
997 childBeforePositive = childRenderBlock->maxPositiveMarginBefore();
998 childBeforeNegative = childRenderBlock->maxNegativeMarginBefore();
999 childAfterPositive = childRenderBlock->maxPositiveMarginAfter();
1000 childAfterNegative = childRenderBlock->maxNegativeMarginAfter();
1001 } else {
1002 beforeMargin = child.marginBefore();
1003 afterMargin = child.marginAfter();
1004 }
1005 } else if (child.isHorizontalWritingMode() == isHorizontalWritingMode()) {
1006 // The child has a different directionality. If the child is parallel, then it's just
1007 // flipped relative to us. We can use the margins for the opposite edges.
1008 if (childRenderBlock) {
1009 childBeforePositive = childRenderBlock->maxPositiveMarginAfter();
1010 childBeforeNegative = childRenderBlock->maxNegativeMarginAfter();
1011 childAfterPositive = childRenderBlock->maxPositiveMarginBefore();
1012 childAfterNegative = childRenderBlock->maxNegativeMarginBefore();
1013 } else {
1014 beforeMargin = child.marginAfter();
1015 afterMargin = child.marginBefore();
1016 }
1017 } else {
1018 // The child is perpendicular to us, which means its margins don't collapse but are on the
1019 // "logical left/right" sides of the child box. We can just return the raw margin in this case.
1020 beforeMargin = marginBeforeForChild(child);
1021 afterMargin = marginAfterForChild(child);
1022 }
1023
1024 // Resolve uncollapsing margins into their positive/negative buckets.
1025 if (beforeMargin) {
1026 if (beforeMargin > 0)
1027 childBeforePositive = beforeMargin;
1028 else
1029 childBeforeNegative = -beforeMargin;
1030 }
1031 if (afterMargin) {
1032 if (afterMargin > 0)
1033 childAfterPositive = afterMargin;
1034 else
1035 childAfterNegative = -afterMargin;
1036 }
1037
1038 return MarginValues(childBeforePositive, childBeforeNegative, childAfterPositive, childAfterNegative);
1039}
1040
1041bool RenderBlockFlow::childrenPreventSelfCollapsing() const
1042{
1043 if (!childrenInline())
1044 return RenderBlock::childrenPreventSelfCollapsing();
1045
1046 return hasLines();
1047}
1048
1049LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::collapseMargins(RenderBox& child, MarginInfo& marginInfo)
1050{
1051 return collapseMarginsWithChildInfo(&child, child.previousSibling(), marginInfo);
1052}
1053
1054LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::collapseMarginsWithChildInfo(RenderBox* child, RenderObject* prevSibling, MarginInfo& marginInfo)
1055{
1056 bool childDiscardMarginBefore = child ? mustDiscardMarginBeforeForChild(*child) : false;
1057 bool childDiscardMarginAfter = child ? mustDiscardMarginAfterForChild(*child) : false;
1058 bool childIsSelfCollapsing = child ? child->isSelfCollapsingBlock() : false;
1059 bool beforeQuirk = child ? hasMarginBeforeQuirk(*child) : false;
1060 bool afterQuirk = child ? hasMarginAfterQuirk(*child) : false;
1061
1062 // The child discards the before margin when the after margin has discarded in the case of a self collapsing block.
1063 childDiscardMarginBefore = childDiscardMarginBefore || (childDiscardMarginAfter && childIsSelfCollapsing);
1064
1065 // Get the four margin values for the child and cache them.
1066 const MarginValues childMargins = child ? marginValuesForChild(*child) : MarginValues(0, 0, 0, 0);
1067
1068 // Get our max pos and neg top margins.
1069 LayoutUnit posTop = childMargins.positiveMarginBefore();
1070 LayoutUnit negTop = childMargins.negativeMarginBefore();
1071
1072 // For self-collapsing blocks, collapse our bottom margins into our
1073 // top to get new posTop and negTop values.
1074 if (childIsSelfCollapsing) {
1075 posTop = std::max(posTop, childMargins.positiveMarginAfter());
1076 negTop = std::max(negTop, childMargins.negativeMarginAfter());
1077 }
1078
1079 if (marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginBefore()) {
1080 if (!childDiscardMarginBefore && !marginInfo.discardMargin()) {
1081 // This child is collapsing with the top of the
1082 // block. If it has larger margin values, then we need to update
1083 // our own maximal values.
1084 if (!document().inQuirksMode() || !marginInfo.quirkContainer() || !beforeQuirk)
1085 setMaxMarginBeforeValues(std::max(posTop, maxPositiveMarginBefore()), std::max(negTop, maxNegativeMarginBefore()));
1086
1087 // The minute any of the margins involved isn't a quirk, don't
1088 // collapse it away, even if the margin is smaller (www.webreference.com
1089 // has an example of this, a <dt> with 0.8em author-specified inside
1090 // a <dl> inside a <td>.
1091 if (!marginInfo.determinedMarginBeforeQuirk() && !beforeQuirk && (posTop - negTop)) {
1092 setHasMarginBeforeQuirk(false);
1093 marginInfo.setDeterminedMarginBeforeQuirk(true);
1094 }
1095
1096 if (!marginInfo.determinedMarginBeforeQuirk() && beforeQuirk && !marginBefore()) {
1097 // We have no top margin and our top child has a quirky margin.
1098 // We will pick up this quirky margin and pass it through.
1099 // This deals with the <td><div><p> case.
1100 // Don't do this for a block that split two inlines though. You do
1101 // still apply margins in this case.
1102 setHasMarginBeforeQuirk(true);
1103 }
1104 } else
1105 // The before margin of the container will also discard all the margins it is collapsing with.
1106 setMustDiscardMarginBefore();
1107 }
1108
1109 // Once we find a child with discardMarginBefore all the margins collapsing with us must also discard.
1110 if (childDiscardMarginBefore) {
1111 marginInfo.setDiscardMargin(true);
1112 marginInfo.clearMargin();
1113 }
1114
1115 if (marginInfo.quirkContainer() && marginInfo.atBeforeSideOfBlock() && (posTop - negTop))
1116 marginInfo.setHasMarginBeforeQuirk(beforeQuirk);
1117
1118 LayoutUnit beforeCollapseLogicalTop = logicalHeight();
1119 LayoutUnit logicalTop = beforeCollapseLogicalTop;
1120
1121 LayoutUnit clearanceForSelfCollapsingBlock;
1122
1123 // If the child's previous sibling is a self-collapsing block that cleared a float then its top border edge has been set at the bottom border edge
1124 // of the float. Since we want to collapse the child's top margin with the self-collapsing block's top and bottom margins we need to adjust our parent's height to match the
1125 // margin top of the self-collapsing block. If the resulting collapsed margin leaves the child still intruding into the float then we will want to clear it.
1126 if (!marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginBefore() && is<RenderBlockFlow>(prevSibling) && downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*prevSibling).isSelfCollapsingBlock()) {
1127 clearanceForSelfCollapsingBlock = downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*prevSibling).marginOffsetForSelfCollapsingBlock();
1128 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() - clearanceForSelfCollapsingBlock);
1129 }
1130
1131 if (childIsSelfCollapsing) {
1132 // For a self collapsing block both the before and after margins get discarded. The block doesn't contribute anything to the height of the block.
1133 // Also, the child's top position equals the logical height of the container.
1134 if (!childDiscardMarginBefore && !marginInfo.discardMargin()) {
1135 // This child has no height. We need to compute our
1136 // position before we collapse the child's margins together,
1137 // so that we can get an accurate position for the zero-height block.
1138 LayoutUnit collapsedBeforePos = std::max(marginInfo.positiveMargin(), childMargins.positiveMarginBefore());
1139 LayoutUnit collapsedBeforeNeg = std::max(marginInfo.negativeMargin(), childMargins.negativeMarginBefore());
1140 marginInfo.setMargin(collapsedBeforePos, collapsedBeforeNeg);
1141
1142 // Now collapse the child's margins together, which means examining our
1143 // bottom margin values as well.
1144 marginInfo.setPositiveMarginIfLarger(childMargins.positiveMarginAfter());
1145 marginInfo.setNegativeMarginIfLarger(childMargins.negativeMarginAfter());
1146
1147 if (!marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginBefore())
1148 // We need to make sure that the position of the self-collapsing block
1149 // is correct, since it could have overflowing content
1150 // that needs to be positioned correctly (e.g., a block that
1151 // had a specified height of 0 but that actually had subcontent).
1152 logicalTop = logicalHeight() + collapsedBeforePos - collapsedBeforeNeg;
1153 }
1154 } else {
1155 if (child && mustSeparateMarginBeforeForChild(*child)) {
1156 ASSERT(!marginInfo.discardMargin() || (marginInfo.discardMargin() && !marginInfo.margin()));
1157 // If we are at the before side of the block and we collapse, ignore the computed margin
1158 // and just add the child margin to the container height. This will correctly position
1159 // the child inside the container.
1160 LayoutUnit separateMargin = !marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginBefore() ? marginInfo.margin() : 0_lu;
1161 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + separateMargin + marginBeforeForChild(*child));
1162 logicalTop = logicalHeight();
1163 } else if (!marginInfo.discardMargin() && (!marginInfo.atBeforeSideOfBlock()
1164 || (!marginInfo.canCollapseMarginBeforeWithChildren()
1165 && (!document().inQuirksMode() || !marginInfo.quirkContainer() || !marginInfo.hasMarginBeforeQuirk())))) {
1166 // We're collapsing with a previous sibling's margins and not
1167 // with the top of the block.
1168 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + std::max(marginInfo.positiveMargin(), posTop) - std::max(marginInfo.negativeMargin(), negTop));
1169 logicalTop = logicalHeight();
1170 }
1171
1172 marginInfo.setDiscardMargin(childDiscardMarginAfter);
1173
1174 if (!marginInfo.discardMargin()) {
1175 marginInfo.setPositiveMargin(childMargins.positiveMarginAfter());
1176 marginInfo.setNegativeMargin(childMargins.negativeMarginAfter());
1177 } else
1178 marginInfo.clearMargin();
1179
1180 if (marginInfo.margin())
1181 marginInfo.setHasMarginAfterQuirk(afterQuirk);
1182 }
1183
1184 // If margins would pull us past the top of the next page, then we need to pull back and pretend like the margins
1185 // collapsed into the page edge.
1186 auto* layoutState = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState();
1187 if (layoutState->isPaginated() && layoutState->pageLogicalHeight() && logicalTop > beforeCollapseLogicalTop
1188 && hasNextPage(beforeCollapseLogicalTop)) {
1189 LayoutUnit oldLogicalTop = logicalTop;
1190 logicalTop = std::min(logicalTop, nextPageLogicalTop(beforeCollapseLogicalTop));
1191 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + (logicalTop - oldLogicalTop));
1192 }
1193
1194 if (is<RenderBlockFlow>(prevSibling) && !prevSibling->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
1195 // If |child| is a self-collapsing block it may have collapsed into a previous sibling and although it hasn't reduced the height of the parent yet
1196 // any floats from the parent will now overhang.
1197 RenderBlockFlow& block = downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*prevSibling);
1198 LayoutUnit oldLogicalHeight = logicalHeight();
1199 setLogicalHeight(logicalTop);
1200 if (block.containsFloats() && !block.avoidsFloats() && (block.logicalTop() + block.lowestFloatLogicalBottom()) > logicalTop)
1201 addOverhangingFloats(block, false);
1202 setLogicalHeight(oldLogicalHeight);
1203
1204 // If |child|'s previous sibling is a self-collapsing block that cleared a float and margin collapsing resulted in |child| moving up
1205 // into the margin area of the self-collapsing block then the float it clears is now intruding into |child|. Layout again so that we can look for
1206 // floats in the parent that overhang |child|'s new logical top.
1207 bool logicalTopIntrudesIntoFloat = clearanceForSelfCollapsingBlock > 0 && logicalTop < beforeCollapseLogicalTop;
1208 if (child && logicalTopIntrudesIntoFloat && containsFloats() && !child->avoidsFloats() && lowestFloatLogicalBottom() > logicalTop)
1209 child->setNeedsLayout();
1210 }
1211
1212 return logicalTop;
1213}
1214
1215LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::clearFloatsIfNeeded(RenderBox& child, MarginInfo& marginInfo, LayoutUnit oldTopPosMargin, LayoutUnit oldTopNegMargin, LayoutUnit yPos)
1216{
1217 LayoutUnit heightIncrease = getClearDelta(child, yPos);
1218 if (!heightIncrease)
1219 return yPos;
1220
1221 if (child.isSelfCollapsingBlock()) {
1222 bool childDiscardMargin = mustDiscardMarginBeforeForChild(child) || mustDiscardMarginAfterForChild(child);
1223
1224 // For self-collapsing blocks that clear, they can still collapse their
1225 // margins with following siblings. Reset the current margins to represent
1226 // the self-collapsing block's margins only.
1227 // If DISCARD is specified for -webkit-margin-collapse, reset the margin values.
1228 MarginValues childMargins = marginValuesForChild(child);
1229 if (!childDiscardMargin) {
1230 marginInfo.setPositiveMargin(std::max(childMargins.positiveMarginBefore(), childMargins.positiveMarginAfter()));
1231 marginInfo.setNegativeMargin(std::max(childMargins.negativeMarginBefore(), childMargins.negativeMarginAfter()));
1232 } else
1233 marginInfo.clearMargin();
1234 marginInfo.setDiscardMargin(childDiscardMargin);
1235
1236 // CSS2.1 states:
1237 // "If the top and bottom margins of an element with clearance are adjoining, its margins collapse with
1238 // the adjoining margins of following siblings but that resulting margin does not collapse with the bottom margin of the parent block."
1239 // So the parent's bottom margin cannot collapse through this block or any subsequent self-collapsing blocks. Check subsequent siblings
1240 // for a block with height - if none is found then don't allow the margins to collapse with the parent.
1241 bool wouldCollapseMarginsWithParent = marginInfo.canCollapseMarginAfterWithChildren();
1242 for (RenderBox* curr = child.nextSiblingBox(); curr && wouldCollapseMarginsWithParent; curr = curr->nextSiblingBox()) {
1243 if (!curr->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned() && !curr->isSelfCollapsingBlock())
1244 wouldCollapseMarginsWithParent = false;
1245 }
1246 if (wouldCollapseMarginsWithParent)
1247 marginInfo.setCanCollapseMarginAfterWithChildren(false);
1248
1249 // For now set the border-top of |child| flush with the bottom border-edge of the float so it can layout any floating or positioned children of
1250 // its own at the correct vertical position. If subsequent siblings attempt to collapse with |child|'s margins in |collapseMargins| we will
1251 // adjust the height of the parent to |child|'s margin top (which if it is positive sits up 'inside' the float it's clearing) so that all three
1252 // margins can collapse at the correct vertical position.
1253 // Per CSS2.1 we need to ensure that any negative margin-top clears |child| beyond the bottom border-edge of the float so that the top border edge of the child
1254 // (i.e. its clearance) is at a position that satisfies the equation: "the amount of clearance is set so that clearance + margin-top = [height of float],
1255 // i.e., clearance = [height of float] - margin-top".
1256 setLogicalHeight(child.logicalTop() + childMargins.negativeMarginBefore());
1257 } else
1258 // Increase our height by the amount we had to clear.
1259 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + heightIncrease);
1260
1261 if (marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginBefore()) {
1262 // We can no longer collapse with the top of the block since a clear
1263 // occurred. The empty blocks collapse into the cleared block.
1264 // FIXME: This isn't quite correct. Need clarification for what to do
1265 // if the height the cleared block is offset by is smaller than the
1266 // margins involved.
1267 setMaxMarginBeforeValues(oldTopPosMargin, oldTopNegMargin);
1268 marginInfo.setAtBeforeSideOfBlock(false);
1269
1270 // In case the child discarded the before margin of the block we need to reset the mustDiscardMarginBefore flag to the initial value.
1271 setMustDiscardMarginBefore(style().marginBeforeCollapse() == MarginCollapse::Discard);
1272 }
1273
1274 return yPos + heightIncrease;
1275}
1276
1277void RenderBlockFlow::marginBeforeEstimateForChild(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit& positiveMarginBefore, LayoutUnit& negativeMarginBefore, bool& discardMarginBefore) const
1278{
1279 // Give up if in quirks mode and we're a body/table cell and the top margin of the child box is quirky.
1280 // Give up if the child specified -webkit-margin-collapse: separate that prevents collapsing.
1281 // FIXME: Use writing mode independent accessor for marginBeforeCollapse.
1282 if ((document().inQuirksMode() && hasMarginAfterQuirk(child) && (isTableCell() || isBody())) || child.style().marginBeforeCollapse() == MarginCollapse::Separate)
1283 return;
1284
1285 // The margins are discarded by a child that specified -webkit-margin-collapse: discard.
1286 // FIXME: Use writing mode independent accessor for marginBeforeCollapse.
1287 if (child.style().marginBeforeCollapse() == MarginCollapse::Discard) {
1288 positiveMarginBefore = 0;
1289 negativeMarginBefore = 0;
1290 discardMarginBefore = true;
1291 return;
1292 }
1293
1294 LayoutUnit beforeChildMargin = marginBeforeForChild(child);
1295 positiveMarginBefore = std::max(positiveMarginBefore, beforeChildMargin);
1296 negativeMarginBefore = std::max(negativeMarginBefore, -beforeChildMargin);
1297
1298 if (!is<RenderBlockFlow>(child))
1299 return;
1300
1301 RenderBlockFlow& childBlock = downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(child);
1302 if (childBlock.childrenInline() || childBlock.isWritingModeRoot())
1303 return;
1304
1305 MarginInfo childMarginInfo(childBlock, childBlock.borderAndPaddingBefore(), childBlock.borderAndPaddingAfter());
1306 if (!childMarginInfo.canCollapseMarginBeforeWithChildren())
1307 return;
1308
1309 RenderBox* grandchildBox = childBlock.firstChildBox();
1310 for (; grandchildBox; grandchildBox = grandchildBox->nextSiblingBox()) {
1311 if (!grandchildBox->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
1312 break;
1313 }
1314
1315 // Give up if there is clearance on the box, since it probably won't collapse into us.
1316 if (!grandchildBox || RenderStyle::usedClear(*grandchildBox) != UsedClear::None)
1317 return;
1318
1319 // Make sure to update the block margins now for the grandchild box so that we're looking at current values.
1320 if (grandchildBox->needsLayout()) {
1321 grandchildBox->computeAndSetBlockDirectionMargins(*this);
1322 if (is<RenderBlock>(*grandchildBox)) {
1323 RenderBlock& grandchildBlock = downcast<RenderBlock>(*grandchildBox);
1324 grandchildBlock.setHasMarginBeforeQuirk(grandchildBox->style().hasMarginBeforeQuirk());
1325 grandchildBlock.setHasMarginAfterQuirk(grandchildBox->style().hasMarginAfterQuirk());
1326 }
1327 }
1328
1329 // Collapse the margin of the grandchild box with our own to produce an estimate.
1330 childBlock.marginBeforeEstimateForChild(*grandchildBox, positiveMarginBefore, negativeMarginBefore, discardMarginBefore);
1331}
1332
1333LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::estimateLogicalTopPosition(RenderBox& child, const MarginInfo& marginInfo, LayoutUnit& estimateWithoutPagination)
1334{
1335 // FIXME: We need to eliminate the estimation of vertical position, because when it's wrong we sometimes trigger a pathological
1336 // relayout if there are intruding floats.
1337 LayoutUnit logicalTopEstimate = logicalHeight();
1338 if (!marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginBefore()) {
1339 LayoutUnit positiveMarginBefore;
1340 LayoutUnit negativeMarginBefore;
1341 bool discardMarginBefore = false;
1342 if (child.selfNeedsLayout()) {
1343 // Try to do a basic estimation of how the collapse is going to go.
1344 marginBeforeEstimateForChild(child, positiveMarginBefore, negativeMarginBefore, discardMarginBefore);
1345 } else {
1346 // Use the cached collapsed margin values from a previous layout. Most of the time they
1347 // will be right.
1348 MarginValues marginValues = marginValuesForChild(child);
1349 positiveMarginBefore = std::max(positiveMarginBefore, marginValues.positiveMarginBefore());
1350 negativeMarginBefore = std::max(negativeMarginBefore, marginValues.negativeMarginBefore());
1351 discardMarginBefore = mustDiscardMarginBeforeForChild(child);
1352 }
1353
1354 // Collapse the result with our current margins.
1355 if (!discardMarginBefore)
1356 logicalTopEstimate += std::max(marginInfo.positiveMargin(), positiveMarginBefore) - std::max(marginInfo.negativeMargin(), negativeMarginBefore);
1357 }
1358
1359 // Adjust logicalTopEstimate down to the next page if the margins are so large that we don't fit on the current
1360 // page.
1361 auto* layoutState = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState();
1362 if (layoutState->isPaginated() && layoutState->pageLogicalHeight() && logicalTopEstimate > logicalHeight()
1363 && hasNextPage(logicalHeight()))
1364 logicalTopEstimate = std::min(logicalTopEstimate, nextPageLogicalTop(logicalHeight()));
1365
1366 logicalTopEstimate += getClearDelta(child, logicalTopEstimate);
1367
1368 estimateWithoutPagination = logicalTopEstimate;
1369
1370 if (layoutState->isPaginated()) {
1371 // If the object has a page or column break value of "before", then we should shift to the top of the next page.
1372 logicalTopEstimate = applyBeforeBreak(child, logicalTopEstimate);
1373
1374 // For replaced elements and scrolled elements, we want to shift them to the next page if they don't fit on the current one.
1375 logicalTopEstimate = adjustForUnsplittableChild(child, logicalTopEstimate);
1376
1377 if (!child.selfNeedsLayout() && is<RenderBlock>(child))
1378 logicalTopEstimate += downcast<RenderBlock>(child).paginationStrut();
1379 }
1380
1381 return logicalTopEstimate;
1382}
1383
1384void RenderBlockFlow::setCollapsedBottomMargin(const MarginInfo& marginInfo)
1385{
1386 if (marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginAfter() && !marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginBefore()) {
1387 // Update the after side margin of the container to discard if the after margin of the last child also discards and we collapse with it.
1388 // Don't update the max margin values because we won't need them anyway.
1389 if (marginInfo.discardMargin()) {
1390 setMustDiscardMarginAfter();
1391 return;
1392 }
1393
1394 // Update our max pos/neg bottom margins, since we collapsed our bottom margins
1395 // with our children.
1396 setMaxMarginAfterValues(std::max(maxPositiveMarginAfter(), marginInfo.positiveMargin()), std::max(maxNegativeMarginAfter(), marginInfo.negativeMargin()));
1397
1398 if (!marginInfo.hasMarginAfterQuirk())
1399 setHasMarginAfterQuirk(false);
1400
1401 if (marginInfo.hasMarginAfterQuirk() && !marginAfter())
1402 // We have no bottom margin and our last child has a quirky margin.
1403 // We will pick up this quirky margin and pass it through.
1404 // This deals with the <td><div><p> case.
1405 setHasMarginAfterQuirk(true);
1406 }
1407}
1408
1409void RenderBlockFlow::handleAfterSideOfBlock(LayoutUnit beforeSide, LayoutUnit afterSide, MarginInfo& marginInfo)
1410{
1411 marginInfo.setAtAfterSideOfBlock(true);
1412
1413 // If our last child was a self-collapsing block with clearance then our logical height is flush with the
1414 // bottom edge of the float that the child clears. The correct vertical position for the margin-collapsing we want
1415 // to perform now is at the child's margin-top - so adjust our height to that position.
1416 RenderObject* lastBlock = lastChild();
1417 if (is<RenderBlockFlow>(lastBlock) && downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*lastBlock).isSelfCollapsingBlock())
1418 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() - downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*lastBlock).marginOffsetForSelfCollapsingBlock());
1419
1420 // If we can't collapse with children then add in the bottom margin.
1421 if (!marginInfo.discardMargin() && (!marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginAfter() && !marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginBefore()
1422 && (!document().inQuirksMode() || !marginInfo.quirkContainer() || !marginInfo.hasMarginAfterQuirk())))
1423 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + marginInfo.margin());
1424
1425 // Now add in our bottom border/padding.
1426 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + afterSide);
1427
1428 // Negative margins can cause our height to shrink below our minimal height (border/padding).
1429 // If this happens, ensure that the computed height is increased to the minimal height.
1430 setLogicalHeight(std::max(logicalHeight(), beforeSide + afterSide));
1431
1432 // Update our bottom collapsed margin info.
1433 setCollapsedBottomMargin(marginInfo);
1434}

1503{
1504 ASSERT(!child.selfNeedsLayout());

1507 if (child.isHorizontalWritingMode() == isHorizontalWritingMode())
1508 return is<RenderBlockFlow>(child) ? downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(child).mustDiscardMarginAfter() : (child.style().marginAfterCollapse() == MarginCollapse::Discard);
1509
1510 // FIXME: We return false here because the implementation is not geometrically complete. We have values only for before/after, not start/end.
1511 // In case the boxes are perpendicular we assume the property is not specified.
1512 return false;
1513}
