1552
1553static bool inNormalFlow(RenderBox& child)
1554{
1555 RenderBlock* curr = child.containingBlock();
1556 while (curr && curr != &child.view()) {
1557 if (curr->isRenderFragmentedFlow())
1558 return true;
1559 if (curr->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
1560 return false;
1561 curr = curr->containingBlock();
1562 }
1563 return true;
1564}
1565
1566LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::applyBeforeBreak(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit logicalOffset)
1567{
1568 // FIXME: Add page break checking here when we support printing.
1569 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
1570 bool isInsideMulticolFlow = fragmentedFlow;
1571 bool checkColumnBreaks = fragmentedFlow && fragmentedFlow->shouldCheckColumnBreaks();
1572 bool checkPageBreaks = !checkColumnBreaks && view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->pageLogicalHeight(); // FIXME: Once columns can print we have to check this.
1573 bool checkFragmentBreaks = false;
1574 bool checkBeforeAlways = (checkColumnBreaks && child.style().breakBefore() == BreakBetween::Column)
1575 || (checkPageBreaks && alwaysPageBreak(child.style().breakBefore()));
1576 if (checkBeforeAlways && inNormalFlow(child) && hasNextPage(logicalOffset, IncludePageBoundary)) {
1577 if (checkColumnBreaks) {
1578 if (isInsideMulticolFlow)
1579 checkFragmentBreaks = true;
1580 }
1581 if (checkFragmentBreaks) {
1582 LayoutUnit offsetBreakAdjustment;
1583 if (fragmentedFlow->addForcedFragmentBreak(this, offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage() + logicalOffset, &child, true, &offsetBreakAdjustment))
1584 return logicalOffset + offsetBreakAdjustment;
1585 }
1586 return nextPageLogicalTop(logicalOffset, IncludePageBoundary);
1587 }
1588 return logicalOffset;
1589}
1590
1591LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::applyAfterBreak(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit logicalOffset, MarginInfo& marginInfo)
1592{
1593 // FIXME: Add page break checking here when we support printing.
1594 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
1595 bool isInsideMulticolFlow = fragmentedFlow;
1596 bool checkColumnBreaks = fragmentedFlow && fragmentedFlow->shouldCheckColumnBreaks();
1597 bool checkPageBreaks = !checkColumnBreaks && view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->pageLogicalHeight(); // FIXME: Once columns can print we have to check this.
1598 bool checkFragmentBreaks = false;
1599 bool checkAfterAlways = (checkColumnBreaks && child.style().breakAfter() == BreakBetween::Column)
1600 || (checkPageBreaks && alwaysPageBreak(child.style().breakAfter()));
1601 if (checkAfterAlways && inNormalFlow(child) && hasNextPage(logicalOffset, IncludePageBoundary)) {
1602 LayoutUnit marginOffset = marginInfo.canCollapseWithMarginBefore() ? 0_lu : marginInfo.margin();
1603
1604 // So our margin doesn't participate in the next collapsing steps.
1605 marginInfo.clearMargin();
1606
1607 if (checkColumnBreaks) {
1608 if (isInsideMulticolFlow)
1609 checkFragmentBreaks = true;
1610 }
1611 if (checkFragmentBreaks) {
1612 LayoutUnit offsetBreakAdjustment;
1613 if (fragmentedFlow->addForcedFragmentBreak(this, offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage() + logicalOffset + marginOffset, &child, false, &offsetBreakAdjustment))
1614 return logicalOffset + marginOffset + offsetBreakAdjustment;
1615 }
1616 return nextPageLogicalTop(logicalOffset, IncludePageBoundary);
1617 }
1618 return logicalOffset;
1619}
1620
1621LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::adjustBlockChildForPagination(LayoutUnit logicalTopAfterClear, LayoutUnit estimateWithoutPagination, RenderBox& child, bool atBeforeSideOfBlock)
1622{
1623 RenderBlock* childRenderBlock = is<RenderBlock>(child) ? &downcast<RenderBlock>(child) : nullptr;
1624
1625 if (estimateWithoutPagination != logicalTopAfterClear) {
1626 // Our guess prior to pagination movement was wrong. Before we attempt to paginate, let's try again at the new
1627 // position.
1628 setLogicalHeight(logicalTopAfterClear);
1629 setLogicalTopForChild(child, logicalTopAfterClear, ApplyLayoutDelta);
1630
1631 if (child.shrinkToAvoidFloats()) {
1632 // The child's width depends on the line width. When the child shifts to clear an item, its width can
1633 // change (because it has more available line width). So mark the item as dirty.
1634 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
1635 }
1636
1637 if (childRenderBlock) {
1638 if (!child.avoidsFloats() && childRenderBlock->containsFloats())
1639 downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*childRenderBlock).markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout();
1640 child.markForPaginationRelayoutIfNeeded();
1641 }
1642
1643 // Our guess was wrong. Make the child lay itself out again.
1644 child.layoutIfNeeded();
1645 }
1646
1647 LayoutUnit oldTop = logicalTopAfterClear;
1648
1649 // If the object has a page or column break value of "before", then we should shift to the top of the next page.
1650 LayoutUnit result = applyBeforeBreak(child, logicalTopAfterClear);
1651
1652 if (pageLogicalHeightForOffset(result)) {
1653 LayoutUnit remainingLogicalHeight = pageRemainingLogicalHeightForOffset(result, ExcludePageBoundary);
1654 LayoutUnit spaceShortage = child.logicalHeight() - remainingLogicalHeight;
1655 if (spaceShortage > 0) {
1656 // If the child crosses a column boundary, report a break, in case nothing inside it has already
1657 // done so. The column balancer needs to know how much it has to stretch the columns to make more
1658 // content fit. If no breaks are reported (but do occur), the balancer will have no clue. FIXME:
1659 // This should be improved, though, because here we just pretend that the child is
1660 // unsplittable. A splittable child, on the other hand, has break opportunities at every position
1661 // where there's no child content, border or padding. In other words, we risk stretching more
1662 // than necessary.
1663 setPageBreak(result, spaceShortage);
1664 }
1665 }
1666
1667 if (shouldApplySizeContainment(child))
1668 adjustSizeContainmentChildForPagination(child, result);
1669
1670 // For replaced elements and scrolled elements, we want to shift them to the next page if they don't fit on the current one.
1671 LayoutUnit logicalTopBeforeUnsplittableAdjustment = result;
1672 LayoutUnit logicalTopAfterUnsplittableAdjustment = adjustForUnsplittableChild(child, result);
1673
1674 LayoutUnit paginationStrut;
1675 LayoutUnit unsplittableAdjustmentDelta = logicalTopAfterUnsplittableAdjustment - logicalTopBeforeUnsplittableAdjustment;
1676 if (unsplittableAdjustmentDelta)
1677 paginationStrut = unsplittableAdjustmentDelta;
1678 else if (childRenderBlock && childRenderBlock->paginationStrut())
1679 paginationStrut = childRenderBlock->paginationStrut();
1680
1681 if (paginationStrut) {
1682 // We are willing to propagate out to our parent block as long as we were at the top of the block prior
1683 // to collapsing our margins, and as long as we didn't clear or move as a result of other pagination.
1684 if (atBeforeSideOfBlock && oldTop == result && !isOutOfFlowPositioned() && !isTableCell()) {
1685 // FIXME: Should really check if we're exceeding the page height before propagating the strut, but we don't
1686 // have all the information to do so (the strut only has the remaining amount to push). Gecko gets this wrong too
1687 // and pushes to the next page anyway, so not too concerned about it.
1688 setPaginationStrut(result + paginationStrut);
1689 if (childRenderBlock)
1690 childRenderBlock->setPaginationStrut(0);
1691 } else
1692 result += paginationStrut;
1693 }
1694
1695 // Similar to how we apply clearance. Boost height() to be the place where we're going to position the child.
1696 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + (result - oldTop));
1697
1698 // Return the final adjusted logical top.
1699 return result;
1700}
1701
1702static inline LayoutUnit calculateMinimumPageHeight(const RenderStyle& renderStyle, LegacyRootInlineBox& lastLine, LayoutUnit lineTop, LayoutUnit lineBottom)
1703{
1704 // We may require a certain minimum number of lines per page in order to satisfy
1705 // orphans and widows, and that may affect the minimum page height.
1706 unsigned lineCount = std::max<unsigned>(renderStyle.hasAutoOrphans() ? 1 : renderStyle.orphans(), renderStyle.hasAutoWidows() ? 1 : renderStyle.widows());
1707 if (lineCount > 1) {
1708 LegacyRootInlineBox* line = &lastLine;
1709 for (unsigned i = 1; i < lineCount && line->prevRootBox(); i++)
1710 line = line->prevRootBox();
1711
1712 // FIXME: Paginating using line overflow isn't all fine. See FIXME in
1713 // adjustLinePositionForPagination() for more details.
1714 LayoutRect overflow = line->logicalVisualOverflowRect(line->lineTop(), line->lineBottom());
1715 lineTop = std::min(line->lineBoxTop(), overflow.y());
1716 }
1717 return lineBottom - lineTop;
1718}
1719
1720static inline bool needsAppleMailPaginationQuirk(LegacyRootInlineBox& lineBox)
1721{
1722 auto& renderer = lineBox.renderer();
1723
1724 if (!renderer.settings().appleMailPaginationQuirkEnabled())
1725 return false;
1726
1727 if (renderer.element() && renderer.element()->idForStyleResolution() == "messageContentContainer")
1728 return true;
1729
1730 return false;
1731}
1732
1733static void clearShouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidowIfNeeded(RenderBlockFlow& blockFlow)
1734{
1735 if (!blockFlow.shouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow())
1736 return;
1737 blockFlow.clearShouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow();
1738 blockFlow.setDidBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow();
1739}
1740
1741void RenderBlockFlow::adjustLinePositionForPagination(LegacyRootInlineBox* lineBox, LayoutUnit& delta, bool& overflowsFragment, RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow)
1742{
1743 // FIXME: For now we paginate using line overflow. This ensures that lines don't overlap at all when we
1744 // put a strut between them for pagination purposes. However, this really isn't the desired rendering, since
1745 // the line on the top of the next page will appear too far down relative to the same kind of line at the top
1746 // of the first column.
1747 //
1748 // The rendering we would like to see is one where the lineTopWithLeading is at the top of the column, and any line overflow
1749 // simply spills out above the top of the column. This effect would match what happens at the top of the first column.
1750 // We can't achieve this rendering, however, until we stop columns from clipping to the column bounds (thus allowing
1751 // for overflow to occur), and then cache visible overflow for each column rect.
1752 //
1753 // Furthermore, the paint we have to do when a column has overflow has to be special. We need to exclude
1754 // content that paints in a previous column (and content that paints in the following column).
1755 //
1756 // For now we'll at least honor the lineTopWithLeading when paginating if it is above the logical top overflow. This will
1757 // at least make positive leading work in typical cases.
1758 //
1759 // FIXME: Another problem with simply moving lines is that the available line width may change (because of floats).
1760 // Technically if the location we move the line to has a different line width than our old position, then we need to dirty the
1761 // line and all following lines.
1762 overflowsFragment = false;
1763 LayoutRect logicalVisualOverflow = lineBox->logicalVisualOverflowRect(lineBox->lineTop(), lineBox->lineBottom());
1764 LayoutUnit logicalOffset = std::min(lineBox->lineBoxTop(), logicalVisualOverflow.y());
1765 LayoutUnit logicalBottom = std::max(lineBox->lineBoxBottom(), logicalVisualOverflow.maxY());
1766 LayoutUnit lineHeight = logicalBottom - logicalOffset;
1767 updateMinimumPageHeight(logicalOffset, calculateMinimumPageHeight(style(), *lineBox, logicalOffset, logicalBottom));
1768 logicalOffset += delta;
1769 lineBox->setPaginationStrut(0);
1770 lineBox->setIsFirstAfterPageBreak(false);
1771 LayoutUnit pageLogicalHeight = pageLogicalHeightForOffset(logicalOffset);
1772 bool hasUniformPageLogicalHeight = !fragmentedFlow || fragmentedFlow->fragmentsHaveUniformLogicalHeight();
1773 // If lineHeight is greater than pageLogicalHeight, but logicalVisualOverflow.height() still fits, we are
1774 // still going to add a strut, so that the visible overflow fits on a single page.
1775 if (!pageLogicalHeight || !hasNextPage(logicalOffset)) {
1776 // FIXME: In case the line aligns with the top of the page (or it's slightly shifted downwards) it will not be marked as the first line in the page.
1777 // From here, the fix is not straightforward because it's not easy to always determine when the current line is the first in the page.
1778 // With no valid page height, we can't possibly accommodate the widow rules.
1779 clearShouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidowIfNeeded(*this);
1780 return;
1781 }
1782
1783 if (hasUniformPageLogicalHeight && logicalVisualOverflow.height() > pageLogicalHeight) {
1784 // We are so tall that we are bigger than a page. Before we give up and just leave the line where it is, try drilling into the
1785 // line and computing a new height that excludes anything we consider "blank space". We will discard margins, descent, and even overflow. If we are
1786 // able to fit with the blank space and overflow excluded, we will give the line its own page with the highest non-blank element being aligned with the
1787 // top of the page.
1788 // FIXME: We are still honoring gigantic margins, which does leave open the possibility of blank pages caused by this heuristic. It remains to be seen whether or not
1789 // this will be a real-world issue. For now we don't try to deal with this problem.
1790 logicalOffset = static_cast<float>(intMaxForLayoutUnit);
1791 logicalBottom = static_cast<float>(intMinForLayoutUnit);
1792 lineBox->computeReplacedAndTextLineTopAndBottom(logicalOffset, logicalBottom);
1793 lineHeight = logicalBottom - logicalOffset;
1794 if (logicalOffset == intMaxForLayoutUnit || lineHeight > pageLogicalHeight) {
1795 // Give up. We're genuinely too big even after excluding blank space and overflow.
1796 clearShouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidowIfNeeded(*this);
1797 return;
1798 }
1799 pageLogicalHeight = pageLogicalHeightForOffset(logicalOffset);
1800 }
1801
1802 LayoutUnit remainingLogicalHeight = pageRemainingLogicalHeightForOffset(logicalOffset, ExcludePageBoundary);
1803 overflowsFragment = (lineHeight > remainingLogicalHeight);
1804
1805 int lineIndex = legacyLineLayout()->lineCountUntil(lineBox);
1806 if (remainingLogicalHeight < lineHeight || (shouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow() && lineBreakToAvoidWidow() == lineIndex)) {
1807 if (lineBreakToAvoidWidow() == lineIndex)
1808 clearShouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidowIfNeeded(*this);
1809 // If we have a non-uniform page height, then we have to shift further possibly.
1810 if (!hasUniformPageLogicalHeight && !pushToNextPageWithMinimumLogicalHeight(remainingLogicalHeight, logicalOffset, lineHeight))
1811 return;
1812 if (lineHeight > pageLogicalHeight) {
1813 // Split the top margin in order to avoid splitting the visible part of the line.
1814 remainingLogicalHeight -= std::min(lineHeight - pageLogicalHeight, std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, logicalVisualOverflow.y() - lineBox->lineBoxTop()));
1815 }
1816 LayoutUnit remainingLogicalHeightAtNewOffset = pageRemainingLogicalHeightForOffset(logicalOffset + remainingLogicalHeight, ExcludePageBoundary);
1817 overflowsFragment = (lineHeight > remainingLogicalHeightAtNewOffset);
1818 LayoutUnit totalLogicalHeight = lineHeight + std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, logicalOffset);
1819 LayoutUnit pageLogicalHeightAtNewOffset = hasUniformPageLogicalHeight ? pageLogicalHeight : pageLogicalHeightForOffset(logicalOffset + remainingLogicalHeight);
1820 setPageBreak(logicalOffset, lineHeight - remainingLogicalHeight);
1821 if (((lineBox == firstRootBox() && totalLogicalHeight < pageLogicalHeightAtNewOffset) || (!style().hasAutoOrphans() && style().orphans() >= lineIndex))
1822 && !isOutOfFlowPositioned() && !isTableCell()) {
1823 auto firstRootBox = this->firstRootBox();
1824 if (!firstRootBox) {
1825 setPaginationStrut(remainingLogicalHeight + logicalOffset);
1826 return;
1827 }
1828 auto firstRootBoxOverflowRect = firstRootBox->logicalVisualOverflowRect(firstRootBox->lineTop(), firstRootBox->lineBottom());
1829 auto firstLineUpperOverhang = std::max(-firstRootBoxOverflowRect.y(), 0_lu);
1830 if (needsAppleMailPaginationQuirk(*lineBox))
1831 return;
1832 setPaginationStrut(remainingLogicalHeight + logicalOffset + firstLineUpperOverhang);
1833 } else {
1834 delta += remainingLogicalHeight;
1835 lineBox->setPaginationStrut(remainingLogicalHeight);
1836 lineBox->setIsFirstAfterPageBreak(true);
1837 }
1838 } else if (remainingLogicalHeight == pageLogicalHeight) {
1839 // We're at the very top of a page or column.
1840 if (lineBox != firstRootBox())
1841 lineBox->setIsFirstAfterPageBreak(true);
1842 if (lineBox != firstRootBox() || offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage())
1843 setPageBreak(logicalOffset, lineHeight);
1844 }
1845}

1890bool RenderBlockFlow::hasNextPage(LayoutUnit logicalOffset, PageBoundaryRule pageBoundaryRule) const
1891{
1892 ASSERT(view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState() && view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->isPaginated());
1893
1894 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
1895 if (!fragmentedFlow)
1896 return true; // Printing and multi-column both make new pages to accommodate content.
1897
1898 // See if we're in the last fragment.
1899 LayoutUnit pageOffset = offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage() + logicalOffset;
1900 RenderFragmentContainer* fragment = fragmentedFlow->fragmentAtBlockOffset(this, pageOffset, true);
1901 if (!fragment)
1902 return false;
1903
1904 if (fragment->isLastFragment())
1905 return fragment->isRenderFragmentContainerSet() || (pageBoundaryRule == IncludePageBoundary && pageOffset == fragment->logicalTopForFragmentedFlowContent());
1906
1907 RenderFragmentContainer* startFragment = nullptr;
1908 RenderFragmentContainer* endFragment = nullptr;
1909 fragmentedFlow->getFragmentRangeForBox(this, startFragment, endFragment);
1910 return (endFragment && fragment != endFragment);
1911}
1912
1913LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::adjustForUnsplittableChild(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit logicalOffset, LayoutUnit childBeforeMargin, LayoutUnit childAfterMargin)
1914{
1915 // When flexboxes are embedded inside a block flow, they don't perform any adjustments for unsplittable
1916 // children. We'll treat flexboxes themselves as unsplittable just to get them to paginate properly inside
1917 // a block flow.
1918 bool isUnsplittable = childBoxIsUnsplittableForFragmentation(child);
1919 if (!isUnsplittable && !(child.isFlexibleBox() && !downcast<RenderFlexibleBox>(child).isFlexibleBoxImpl()))
1920 return logicalOffset;
1921
1922 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
1923 LayoutUnit childLogicalHeight = logicalHeightForChild(child) + childBeforeMargin + childAfterMargin;
1924 LayoutUnit pageLogicalHeight = pageLogicalHeightForOffset(logicalOffset);
1925 bool hasUniformPageLogicalHeight = !fragmentedFlow || fragmentedFlow->fragmentsHaveUniformLogicalHeight();
1926 if (isUnsplittable)
1927 updateMinimumPageHeight(logicalOffset, childLogicalHeight);
1928 if (!pageLogicalHeight || (hasUniformPageLogicalHeight && childLogicalHeight > pageLogicalHeight)
1929 || !hasNextPage(logicalOffset))
1930 return logicalOffset;
1931 LayoutUnit remainingLogicalHeight = pageRemainingLogicalHeightForOffset(logicalOffset, ExcludePageBoundary);
1932 if (remainingLogicalHeight < childLogicalHeight) {
1933 if (!hasUniformPageLogicalHeight && !pushToNextPageWithMinimumLogicalHeight(remainingLogicalHeight, logicalOffset, childLogicalHeight))
1934 return logicalOffset;
1935 auto result = logicalOffset + remainingLogicalHeight;
1936 bool isInitialLetter = child.isFloating() && child.style().styleType() == PseudoId::FirstLetter && child.style().initialLetterDrop() > 0;
1937 if (isInitialLetter) {
1938 // Increase our logical height to ensure that lines all get pushed along with the letter.
1939 setLogicalHeight(logicalOffset + remainingLogicalHeight);
1940 }
1941 return result;
1942 }
1943
1944 return logicalOffset;
1945}
1946
1947bool RenderBlockFlow::pushToNextPageWithMinimumLogicalHeight(LayoutUnit& adjustment, LayoutUnit logicalOffset, LayoutUnit minimumLogicalHeight) const
1948{
1949 bool checkFragment = false;
1950 auto* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
1951 RenderFragmentContainer* currentFragmentContainer = nullptr;
1952 for (auto pageLogicalHeight = pageLogicalHeightForOffset(logicalOffset + adjustment); pageLogicalHeight; pageLogicalHeight = pageLogicalHeightForOffset(logicalOffset + adjustment)) {
1953 if (minimumLogicalHeight <= pageLogicalHeight)
1954 return true;
1955 auto adjustedOffset = logicalOffset + adjustment;
1956 if (!hasNextPage(adjustedOffset))
1957 return false;
1958 if (fragmentedFlow) {
1959 // While in layout and the columnsets are not balanced yet, we keep finding the same (infinite tall) column over and over again.
1960 auto* nextFragmentContainer = fragmentedFlow->fragmentAtBlockOffset(this, adjustedOffset, true);
1961 ASSERT(nextFragmentContainer);
1962 if (nextFragmentContainer == currentFragmentContainer)
1963 return false;
1964 currentFragmentContainer = nextFragmentContainer;
1965 }
1966 adjustment += pageLogicalHeight;
1967 checkFragment = true;
1968 }
1969 return !checkFragment;
1970}

1984LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::nextPageLogicalTop(LayoutUnit logicalOffset, PageBoundaryRule pageBoundaryRule) const
1985{
1986 LayoutUnit pageLogicalHeight = pageLogicalHeightForOffset(logicalOffset);
1987 if (!pageLogicalHeight)
1988 return logicalOffset;
1989
1990 // The logicalOffset is in our coordinate space. We can add in our pushed offset.
1991 LayoutUnit remainingLogicalHeight = pageRemainingLogicalHeightForOffset(logicalOffset);
1992 if (pageBoundaryRule == ExcludePageBoundary)
1993 return logicalOffset + (remainingLogicalHeight ? remainingLogicalHeight : pageLogicalHeight);
1994 return logicalOffset + remainingLogicalHeight;
1995}
1996
1997LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::pageLogicalTopForOffset(LayoutUnit offset) const
1998{
1999 // Unsplittable objects clear out the pageLogicalHeight in the layout state as a way of signaling that no
2000 // pagination should occur. Therefore we have to check this first and bail if the value has been set to 0.
2001 auto* layoutState = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState();
2002 LayoutUnit pageLogicalHeight = layoutState->pageLogicalHeight();
2003 if (!pageLogicalHeight)
2004 return 0;
2005
2006 LayoutUnit firstPageLogicalTop = isHorizontalWritingMode() ? layoutState->pageOffset().height() : layoutState->pageOffset().width();
2007 LayoutUnit blockLogicalTop = isHorizontalWritingMode() ? layoutState->layoutOffset().height() : layoutState->layoutOffset().width();
2008
2009 LayoutUnit cumulativeOffset = offset + blockLogicalTop;
2010 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2011 if (!fragmentedFlow)
2012 return cumulativeOffset - roundToInt(cumulativeOffset - firstPageLogicalTop) % roundToInt(pageLogicalHeight);
2013 return firstPageLogicalTop + fragmentedFlow->pageLogicalTopForOffset(cumulativeOffset - firstPageLogicalTop);
2014}
2015
2016LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::pageLogicalHeightForOffset(LayoutUnit offset) const
2017{
2018 // Unsplittable objects clear out the pageLogicalHeight in the layout state as a way of signaling that no
2019 // pagination should occur. Therefore we have to check this first and bail if the value has been set to 0.
2020 LayoutUnit pageLogicalHeight = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->pageLogicalHeight();
2021 if (!pageLogicalHeight)
2022 return 0;
2023
2024 // Now check for a flow thread.
2025 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2026 if (!fragmentedFlow)
2027 return pageLogicalHeight;
2028 return fragmentedFlow->pageLogicalHeightForOffset(offset + offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage());
2029}
2030
2031LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::pageRemainingLogicalHeightForOffset(LayoutUnit offset, PageBoundaryRule pageBoundaryRule) const
2032{
2033 offset += offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage();
2034
2035 RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2036 if (!fragmentedFlow) {
2037 LayoutUnit pageLogicalHeight = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->pageLogicalHeight();
2038 LayoutUnit remainingHeight = pageLogicalHeight - intMod(offset, pageLogicalHeight);
2039 if (pageBoundaryRule == IncludePageBoundary) {
2040 // If includeBoundaryPoint is true the line exactly on the top edge of a
2041 // column will act as being part of the previous column.
2042 remainingHeight = intMod(remainingHeight, pageLogicalHeight);
2043 }
2044 return remainingHeight;
2045 }
2046
2047 return fragmentedFlow->pageRemainingLogicalHeightForOffset(offset, pageBoundaryRule);
2048}

2052 return logicalHeightForChild(child);

2055void RenderBlockFlow::adjustSizeContainmentChildForPagination(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit offset)
2056{
2057 if (!shouldApplySizeContainment(child))
2058 return;
2059
2060 LayoutUnit childOverflowHeight = child.isHorizontalWritingMode() ? child.layoutOverflowRect().maxY() : child.layoutOverflowRect().maxX();
2061 LayoutUnit childLogicalHeight = std::max(child.logicalHeight(), childOverflowHeight);
2062
2063 LayoutUnit remainingLogicalHeight = pageRemainingLogicalHeightForOffset(offset, ExcludePageBoundary);
2064
2065 LayoutUnit spaceShortage = childLogicalHeight - remainingLogicalHeight;
2066 if (spaceShortage <= 0)
2067 return;
2068
2069 if (RenderFragmentedFlow* fragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow())
2070 fragmentedFlow->updateSpaceShortageForSizeContainment(this, offsetFromLogicalTopOfFirstPage() + offset, spaceShortage);
2071}

2100
2101void RenderBlockFlow::styleDidChange(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle* oldStyle)
2102{
2103 RenderBlock::styleDidChange(diff, oldStyle);
2104
2105 // After our style changed, if we lose our ability to propagate floats into next sibling
2106 // blocks, then we need to find the top most parent containing that overhanging float and
2107 // then mark its descendants with floats for layout and clear all floats from its next
2108 // sibling blocks that exist in our floating objects list. See bug 56299 and 62875.
2109 bool canPropagateFloatIntoSibling = !isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned() && !avoidsFloats();
2110 if (diff == StyleDifference::Layout && s_canPropagateFloatIntoSibling && !canPropagateFloatIntoSibling && hasOverhangingFloats()) {
2111 RenderBlockFlow* parentBlock = this;
2112 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_floatingObjects->set();
2113
2114 for (auto& ancestor : ancestorsOfType<RenderBlockFlow>(*this)) {
2115 if (ancestor.isRenderView())
2116 break;
2117 if (ancestor.hasOverhangingFloats()) {
2118 for (auto it = floatingObjectSet.begin(), end = floatingObjectSet.end(); it != end; ++it) {
2119 RenderBox& renderer = (*it)->renderer();
2120 if (ancestor.hasOverhangingFloat(renderer)) {
2121 parentBlock = &ancestor;
2122 break;
2123 }
2124 }
2125 }
2126 }
2127
2128 parentBlock->markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout();
2129 parentBlock->markSiblingsWithFloatsForLayout();
2130 }
2131
2132 if (diff >= StyleDifference::Repaint) {
2133 auto shouldInvalidateLineLayoutPath = [&] {
2134 if (selfNeedsLayout() || legacyLineLayout())
2135 return true;
2136#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
2137 if (modernLineLayout() && !LayoutIntegration::LineLayout::canUseForAfterStyleChange(*this, diff))
2138 return true;
2139#endif
2140 return false;
2141 };
2142 if (shouldInvalidateLineLayoutPath())
2143 invalidateLineLayoutPath();
2144
2145#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
2146 if (auto* lineLayout = modernLineLayout())
2147 lineLayout->updateStyle(*this);
2148#endif
2149 }
2150
2151 if (multiColumnFlow())
2152 updateStylesForColumnChildren();
2153}
2154
2155void RenderBlockFlow::updateStylesForColumnChildren()
2156{
2157 for (auto* child = firstChildBox(); child && (child->isRenderFragmentedFlow() || child->isRenderMultiColumnSet()); child = child->nextSiblingBox())
2158 child->setStyle(RenderStyle::createAnonymousStyleWithDisplay(style(), DisplayType::Block));
2159}

2161void RenderBlockFlow::styleWillChange(StyleDifference diff, const RenderStyle& newStyle)
2162{
2163 const RenderStyle* oldStyle = hasInitializedStyle() ? &style() : nullptr;
2164 s_canPropagateFloatIntoSibling = oldStyle ? !isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned() && !avoidsFloats() : false;
2165
2166 if (oldStyle) {
2167 auto oldPosition = oldStyle->position();
2168 auto newPosition = newStyle.position();
2169
2170 if (parent() && diff == StyleDifference::Layout && oldPosition != newPosition) {
2171 if (containsFloats() && !isFloating() && !isOutOfFlowPositioned() && newStyle.hasOutOfFlowPosition())
2172 markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout();
2173 }
2174 }

2185
2186void RenderBlockFlow::addFloatsToNewParent(RenderBlockFlow& toBlockFlow) const
2187{
2188 // When a portion of the render tree is being detached, anonymous blocks
2189 // will be combined as their children are deleted. In this process, the
2190 // anonymous block later in the tree is merged into the one preceeding it.
2191 // It can happen that the later block (this) contains floats that the
2192 // previous block (toBlockFlow) did not contain, and thus are not in the
2193 // floating objects list for toBlockFlow. This can result in toBlockFlow
2194 // containing floats that are not in it's floating objects list, but are in
2195 // the floating objects lists of siblings and parents. This can cause
2196 // problems when the float itself is deleted, since the deletion code
2197 // assumes that if a float is not in it's containing block's floating
2198 // objects list, it isn't in any floating objects list. In order to
2199 // preserve this condition (removing it has serious performance
2200 // implications), we need to copy the floating objects from the old block
2201 // (this) to the new block (toBlockFlow). The float's metrics will likely
2202 // all be wrong, but since toBlockFlow is already marked for layout, this
2203 // will get fixed before anything gets displayed.
2204 // See bug https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=115566
2205 if (!m_floatingObjects)
2206 return;
2207

2341FloatingObject* RenderBlockFlow::insertFloatingObject(RenderBox& floatBox)
2342{
2343 ASSERT(floatBox.isFloating());
2344
2345 // Create the list of special objects if we don't aleady have one
2346 if (!m_floatingObjects)
2347 createFloatingObjects();
2348 else {
2349 // Don't insert the floatingObject again if it's already in the list
2350 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_floatingObjects->set();
2351 auto it = floatingObjectSet.find<FloatingObjectHashTranslator>(floatBox);
2352 if (it != floatingObjectSet.end())
2353 return it->get();
2354 }
2355
2356 // Create the special floatingObject entry & append it to the list
2357
2358 std::unique_ptr<FloatingObject> floatingObject = FloatingObject::create(floatBox);
2359
2360 // Our location is irrelevant if we're unsplittable or no pagination is in effect. Just lay out the float.
2361 bool isChildRenderBlock = floatBox.isRenderBlock();
2362 if (isChildRenderBlock && !floatBox.needsLayout() && view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->pageLogicalHeightChanged())
2363 floatBox.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
2364
2365 bool needsBlockDirectionLocationSetBeforeLayout = isChildRenderBlock && view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->needsBlockDirectionLocationSetBeforeLayout();
2366 if (!needsBlockDirectionLocationSetBeforeLayout || isWritingModeRoot()) {
2367 // We are unsplittable if we're a block flow root.
2368 floatBox.layoutIfNeeded();
2369 } else {
2370 floatBox.updateLogicalWidth();
2371 floatBox.computeAndSetBlockDirectionMargins(*this);
2372 }
2373
2374 setLogicalWidthForFloat(*floatingObject, logicalWidthForChild(floatBox) + marginStartForChild(floatBox) + marginEndForChild(floatBox));
2375
2376 return m_floatingObjects->add(WTFMove(floatingObject));
2377}

2379void RenderBlockFlow::removeFloatingObject(RenderBox& floatBox)
2380{
2381 if (m_floatingObjects) {
2382 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_floatingObjects->set();
2383 auto it = floatingObjectSet.find<FloatingObjectHashTranslator>(floatBox);
2384 if (it != floatingObjectSet.end()) {
2385 auto& floatingObject = *it->get();
2386 if (childrenInline()) {
2387 LayoutUnit logicalTop = logicalTopForFloat(floatingObject);
2388 LayoutUnit logicalBottom = logicalBottomForFloat(floatingObject);
2389
2390 // Fix for https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=54995.
2391 if (logicalBottom < 0 || logicalBottom < logicalTop || logicalTop == LayoutUnit::max())
2392 logicalBottom = LayoutUnit::max();
2393 else {
2394 // Special-case zero- and less-than-zero-height floats: those don't touch
2395 // the line that they're on, but it still needs to be dirtied. This is
2396 // accomplished by pretending they have a height of 1.
2397 logicalBottom = std::max(logicalBottom, logicalTop + 1);
2398 }
2399 if (floatingObject.originatingLine()) {
2400 floatingObject.originatingLine()->removeFloat(floatBox);
2401 if (!selfNeedsLayout()) {
2402 ASSERT(&floatingObject.originatingLine()->renderer() == this);
2403 floatingObject.originatingLine()->markDirty();
2404 }
2405#if ASSERT_ENABLED
2406 floatingObject.clearOriginatingLine();
2407#endif
2408 }
2409 markLinesDirtyInBlockRange(0, logicalBottom);
2410 }
2411 m_floatingObjects->remove(&floatingObject);
2412 }
2413 }

2447void RenderBlockFlow::computeLogicalLocationForFloat(FloatingObject& floatingObject, LayoutUnit& logicalTopOffset)
2448{
2449 auto& childBox = floatingObject.renderer();
2450 LayoutUnit logicalLeftOffset = logicalLeftOffsetForContent(logicalTopOffset); // Constant part of left offset.
2451 LayoutUnit logicalRightOffset = logicalRightOffsetForContent(logicalTopOffset); // Constant part of right offset.
2452
2453 LayoutUnit floatLogicalWidth = std::min(logicalWidthForFloat(floatingObject), logicalRightOffset - logicalLeftOffset); // The width we look for.
2454
2455 LayoutUnit floatLogicalLeft;
2456
2457 bool insideFragmentedFlow = enclosingFragmentedFlow();
2458 bool isInitialLetter = childBox.style().styleType() == PseudoId::FirstLetter && childBox.style().initialLetterDrop() > 0;
2459
2460 if (isInitialLetter) {
2461 int letterClearance = lowestInitialLetterLogicalBottom() - logicalTopOffset;
2462 if (letterClearance > 0) {
2463 logicalTopOffset += letterClearance;
2464 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + letterClearance);
2465 }
2466 }
2467
2468 if (RenderStyle::usedFloat(childBox) == UsedFloat::Left) {
2469 LayoutUnit heightRemainingLeft = 1_lu;
2470 LayoutUnit heightRemainingRight = 1_lu;
2471 floatLogicalLeft = logicalLeftOffsetForPositioningFloat(logicalTopOffset, logicalLeftOffset, false, &heightRemainingLeft);
2472 while (logicalRightOffsetForPositioningFloat(logicalTopOffset, logicalRightOffset, false, &heightRemainingRight) - floatLogicalLeft < floatLogicalWidth) {
2473 logicalTopOffset += std::min(heightRemainingLeft, heightRemainingRight);
2474 floatLogicalLeft = logicalLeftOffsetForPositioningFloat(logicalTopOffset, logicalLeftOffset, false, &heightRemainingLeft);
2475 if (insideFragmentedFlow) {
2476 // Have to re-evaluate all of our offsets, since they may have changed.
2477 logicalRightOffset = logicalRightOffsetForContent(logicalTopOffset); // Constant part of right offset.
2478 logicalLeftOffset = logicalLeftOffsetForContent(logicalTopOffset); // Constant part of left offset.
2479 floatLogicalWidth = std::min(logicalWidthForFloat(floatingObject), logicalRightOffset - logicalLeftOffset);
2480 }
2481 }
2482 floatLogicalLeft = std::max(logicalLeftOffset - borderAndPaddingLogicalLeft(), floatLogicalLeft);
2483 } else {
2484 LayoutUnit heightRemainingLeft = 1_lu;
2485 LayoutUnit heightRemainingRight = 1_lu;
2486 floatLogicalLeft = logicalRightOffsetForPositioningFloat(logicalTopOffset, logicalRightOffset, false, &heightRemainingRight);
2487 while (floatLogicalLeft - logicalLeftOffsetForPositioningFloat(logicalTopOffset, logicalLeftOffset, false, &heightRemainingLeft) < floatLogicalWidth) {
2488 logicalTopOffset += std::min(heightRemainingLeft, heightRemainingRight);
2489 floatLogicalLeft = logicalRightOffsetForPositioningFloat(logicalTopOffset, logicalRightOffset, false, &heightRemainingRight);
2490 if (insideFragmentedFlow) {
2491 // Have to re-evaluate all of our offsets, since they may have changed.
2492 logicalRightOffset = logicalRightOffsetForContent(logicalTopOffset); // Constant part of right offset.
2493 logicalLeftOffset = logicalLeftOffsetForContent(logicalTopOffset); // Constant part of left offset.
2494 floatLogicalWidth = std::min(logicalWidthForFloat(floatingObject), logicalRightOffset - logicalLeftOffset);
2495 }
2496 }
2497 // Use the original width of the float here, since the local variable
2498 // |floatLogicalWidth| was capped to the available line width. See
2499 // fast/block/float/clamped-right-float.html.
2500 floatLogicalLeft -= logicalWidthForFloat(floatingObject);
2501 }
2502
2503 LayoutUnit childLogicalLeftMargin = style().isLeftToRightDirection() ? marginStartForChild(childBox) : marginEndForChild(childBox);
2504 LayoutUnit childBeforeMargin = marginBeforeForChild(childBox);
2505
2506 if (isInitialLetter)
2507 adjustInitialLetterPosition(childBox, logicalTopOffset, childBeforeMargin);
2508
2509 setLogicalLeftForFloat(floatingObject, floatLogicalLeft);
2510 setLogicalLeftForChild(childBox, floatLogicalLeft + childLogicalLeftMargin);
2511
2512 setLogicalTopForFloat(floatingObject, logicalTopOffset);
2513 setLogicalTopForChild(childBox, logicalTopOffset + childBeforeMargin);
2514
2515 setLogicalMarginsForFloat(floatingObject, childLogicalLeftMargin, childBeforeMargin);
2516}
2517
2518void RenderBlockFlow::adjustInitialLetterPosition(RenderBox& childBox, LayoutUnit& logicalTopOffset, LayoutUnit& marginBeforeOffset)
2519{
2520 const RenderStyle& style = firstLineStyle();
2521 const FontMetrics& fontMetrics = style.fontMetrics();
2522 if (!fontMetrics.hasCapHeight())
2523 return;
2524
2525 LayoutUnit heightOfLine = lineHeight(true, isHorizontalWritingMode() ? HorizontalLine : VerticalLine, PositionOfInteriorLineBoxes);
2526 LayoutUnit beforeMarginBorderPadding = childBox.borderAndPaddingBefore() + childBox.marginBefore();
2527
2528 // Make an adjustment to align with the cap height of a theoretical block line.
2529 LayoutUnit adjustment = fontMetrics.ascent() + (heightOfLine - fontMetrics.height()) / 2 - fontMetrics.capHeight() - beforeMarginBorderPadding;
2530 logicalTopOffset += adjustment;
2531
2532 // For sunken and raised caps, we have to make some adjustments. Test if we're sunken or raised (dropHeightDelta will be
2533 // positive for raised and negative for sunken).
2534 int dropHeightDelta = childBox.style().initialLetterHeight() - childBox.style().initialLetterDrop();
2535
2536 // If we're sunken, the float needs to shift down but lines still need to avoid it. In order to do that we increase the float's margin.
2537 if (dropHeightDelta < 0)
2538 marginBeforeOffset += -dropHeightDelta * heightOfLine;
2539
2540 // If we're raised, then we actually have to grow the height of the block, since the lines have to be pushed down as though we're placing
2541 // empty lines beside the first letter.
2542 if (dropHeightDelta > 0)
2543 setLogicalHeight(logicalHeight() + dropHeightDelta * heightOfLine);
2544}
2545
2546bool RenderBlockFlow::positionNewFloats()
2547{
2548 if (!m_floatingObjects)
2549 return false;
2550
2551 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_floatingObjects->set();
2552 if (floatingObjectSet.isEmpty())
2553 return false;
2554
2555 // If all floats have already been positioned, then we have no work to do.
2556 if (floatingObjectSet.last()->isPlaced())
2557 return false;
2558
2559 // Move backwards through our floating object list until we find a float that has
2560 // already been positioned. Then we'll be able to move forward, positioning all of
2561 // the new floats that need it.
2562 auto it = floatingObjectSet.end();
2563 --it; // Go to last item.
2564 auto begin = floatingObjectSet.begin();
2565 FloatingObject* lastPlacedFloatingObject = 0;
2566 while (it != begin) {
2567 --it;
2568 if ((*it)->isPlaced()) {
2569 lastPlacedFloatingObject = it->get();
2570 ++it;
2571 break;
2572 }
2573 }
2574
2575 LayoutUnit logicalTop = logicalHeight();
2576
2577 // The float cannot start above the top position of the last positioned float.
2578 if (lastPlacedFloatingObject)
2579 logicalTop = std::max(logicalTopForFloat(*lastPlacedFloatingObject), logicalTop);
2580
2581 auto end = floatingObjectSet.end();
2582 // Now walk through the set of unpositioned floats and place them.
2583 for (; it != end; ++it) {
2584 auto& floatingObject = *it->get();
2585 // The containing block is responsible for positioning floats, so if we have floats in our
2586 // list that come from somewhere else, do not attempt to position them.
2587 auto& childBox = floatingObject.renderer();
2588 if (childBox.containingBlock() != this)
2589 continue;
2590
2591 LayoutRect oldRect = childBox.frameRect();
2592 auto childBoxUsedClear = RenderStyle::usedClear(childBox);
2593 if (childBoxUsedClear == UsedClear::Left || childBoxUsedClear == UsedClear::Both)
2594 logicalTop = std::max(lowestFloatLogicalBottom(FloatingObject::FloatLeft), logicalTop);
2595 if (childBoxUsedClear == UsedClear::Right || childBoxUsedClear == UsedClear::Both)
2596 logicalTop = std::max(lowestFloatLogicalBottom(FloatingObject::FloatRight), logicalTop);
2597
2598 computeLogicalLocationForFloat(floatingObject, logicalTop);
2599 LayoutUnit childLogicalTop = logicalTopForChild(childBox);
2600
2601 estimateFragmentRangeForBoxChild(childBox);
2602
2603 childBox.markForPaginationRelayoutIfNeeded();
2604 childBox.layoutIfNeeded();
2605
2606 auto* layoutState = view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState();
2607 bool isPaginated = layoutState->isPaginated();
2608 if (isPaginated) {
2609 // If we are unsplittable and don't fit, then we need to move down.
2610 // We include our margins as part of the unsplittable area.
2611 LayoutUnit newLogicalTop = adjustForUnsplittableChild(childBox, logicalTop, childLogicalTop - logicalTop, marginAfterForChild(childBox));
2612
2613 // See if we have a pagination strut that is making us move down further.
2614 // Note that an unsplittable child can't also have a pagination strut, so this
2615 // is exclusive with the case above.
2616 RenderBlock* childBlock = is<RenderBlock>(childBox) ? &downcast<RenderBlock>(childBox) : nullptr;
2617 if (childBlock && childBlock->paginationStrut()) {
2618 newLogicalTop += childBlock->paginationStrut();
2619 childBlock->setPaginationStrut(0);
2620 }
2621
2622 if (newLogicalTop != logicalTop) {
2623 floatingObject.setPaginationStrut(newLogicalTop - logicalTop);
2624 computeLogicalLocationForFloat(floatingObject, newLogicalTop);
2625 if (childBlock)
2626 childBlock->setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
2627 childBox.layoutIfNeeded();
2628 logicalTop = newLogicalTop;
2629 }
2630
2631 if (updateFragmentRangeForBoxChild(childBox)) {
2632 childBox.setNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
2633 childBox.layoutIfNeeded();
2634 }
2635 }
2636
2637 setLogicalHeightForFloat(floatingObject, logicalHeightForChildForFragmentation(childBox) + (logicalTopForChild(childBox) - logicalTop) + marginAfterForChild(childBox));
2638
2639 m_floatingObjects->addPlacedObject(&floatingObject);
2640
2641 if (ShapeOutsideInfo* shapeOutside = childBox.shapeOutsideInfo())
2642 shapeOutside->setReferenceBoxLogicalSize(logicalSizeForChild(childBox));
2643 // If the child moved, we have to repaint it.
2644 if (childBox.checkForRepaintDuringLayout())
2645 childBox.repaintDuringLayoutIfMoved(oldRect);
2646 }
2647 return true;
2648}

2650void RenderBlockFlow::clearFloats(UsedClear usedClear)
2651{
2652 positionNewFloats();
2653 // set y position
2654 LayoutUnit newY;
2655 switch (usedClear) {
2656 case UsedClear::Left:
2657 newY = lowestFloatLogicalBottom(FloatingObject::FloatLeft);
2658 break;
2659 case UsedClear::Right:
2660 newY = lowestFloatLogicalBottom(FloatingObject::FloatRight);
2661 break;
2662 case UsedClear::Both:
2663 newY = lowestFloatLogicalBottom();
2664 break;
2665 case UsedClear::None:
2666 break;
2667 }
2668 // FIXME: The float search tree has floored float box position (see FloatingObjects::intervalForFloatingObject).
2669 newY = newY.floor();
2670 if (height() < newY)
2671 setLogicalHeight(newY);
2672}

2735
2736LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::addOverhangingFloats(RenderBlockFlow& child, bool makeChildPaintOtherFloats)
2737{
2738 // Prevent floats from being added to the canvas by the root element, e.g., <html>.
2739 if (!child.containsFloats() || child.createsNewFormattingContext())
2740 return 0;
2741
2742 LayoutUnit childLogicalTop = child.logicalTop();
2743 LayoutUnit childLogicalLeft = child.logicalLeft();
2744 LayoutUnit lowestFloatLogicalBottom;
2745
2746 // Floats that will remain the child's responsibility to paint should factor into its
2747 // overflow.
2748 auto childEnd = child.m_floatingObjects->set().end();
2749 for (auto childIt = child.m_floatingObjects->set().begin(); childIt != childEnd; ++childIt) {
2750 auto& floatingObject = *childIt->get();
2751 LayoutUnit floatLogicalBottom = std::min(logicalBottomForFloat(floatingObject), LayoutUnit::max() - childLogicalTop);
2752 LayoutUnit logicalBottom = childLogicalTop + floatLogicalBottom;
2753 lowestFloatLogicalBottom = std::max(lowestFloatLogicalBottom, logicalBottom);
2754
2755 if (logicalBottom > logicalHeight()) {
2756 // If the object is not in the list, we add it now.
2757 if (!containsFloat(floatingObject.renderer())) {
2758 LayoutSize offset = isHorizontalWritingMode() ? LayoutSize(-childLogicalLeft, -childLogicalTop) : LayoutSize(-childLogicalTop, -childLogicalLeft);
2759 bool shouldPaint = false;
2760
2761 // The nearest enclosing layer always paints the float (so that zindex and stacking
2762 // behaves properly). We always want to propagate the desire to paint the float as
2763 // far out as we can, to the outermost block that overlaps the float, stopping only
2764 // if we hit a self-painting layer boundary.
2765 if (floatingObject.renderer().enclosingFloatPaintingLayer() == enclosingFloatPaintingLayer()) {
2766 floatingObject.setPaintsFloat(false);
2767 shouldPaint = true;
2768 }
2769 // We create the floating object list lazily.
2770 if (!m_floatingObjects)
2771 createFloatingObjects();
2772
2773 m_floatingObjects->add(floatingObject.copyToNewContainer(offset, shouldPaint, true));
2774 }
2775 } else {
2776 const auto& renderer = floatingObject.renderer();
2777 if (makeChildPaintOtherFloats && !floatingObject.paintsFloat() && !renderer.hasSelfPaintingLayer()
2778 && renderer.isDescendantOf(&child) && renderer.enclosingFloatPaintingLayer() == child.enclosingFloatPaintingLayer()) {
2779 // The float is not overhanging from this block, so if it is a descendant of the child, the child should
2780 // paint it (the other case is that it is intruding into the child), unless it has its own layer or enclosing
2781 // layer.
2782 // If makeChildPaintOtherFloats is false, it means that the child must already know about all the floats
2783 // it should paint.
2784 floatingObject.setPaintsFloat(true);
2785 }
2786
2787 // Since the float doesn't overhang, it didn't get put into our list. We need to add its overflow in to the child now.
2788 if (floatingObject.isDescendant())
2789 child.addOverflowFromChild(&renderer, floatingObject.locationOffsetOfBorderBox());
2790 }
2791 }
2792 return lowestFloatLogicalBottom;
2793}
2794
2795bool RenderBlockFlow::hasOverhangingFloat(RenderBox& renderer)
2796{
2797 if (!m_floatingObjects || !parent())
2798 return false;
2799
2800 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_floatingObjects->set();
2801 const auto it = floatingObjectSet.find<FloatingObjectHashTranslator>(renderer);
2802 if (it == floatingObjectSet.end())
2803 return false;
2804
2805 return logicalBottomForFloat(*it->get()) > logicalHeight();
2806}
2807
2808void RenderBlockFlow::addIntrudingFloats(RenderBlockFlow* prev, RenderBlockFlow* container, LayoutUnit logicalLeftOffset, LayoutUnit logicalTopOffset)
2809{
2810 ASSERT(!avoidsFloats());
2811
2812 // If we create our own block formatting context then our contents don't interact with floats outside it, even those from our parent.
2813 if (createsNewFormattingContext())
2814 return;
2815
2816 // If the parent or previous sibling doesn't have any floats to add, don't bother.
2817 if (!prev->m_floatingObjects)
2818 return;
2819
2820 logicalLeftOffset += marginLogicalLeft();
2821
2822 const FloatingObjectSet& prevSet = prev->m_floatingObjects->set();
2823 auto prevEnd = prevSet.end();
2824 for (auto prevIt = prevSet.begin(); prevIt != prevEnd; ++prevIt) {
2825 auto& floatingObject = *prevIt->get();
2826 if (logicalBottomForFloat(floatingObject) > logicalTopOffset) {
2827 if (!m_floatingObjects || !m_floatingObjects->set().contains(&floatingObject)) {
2828 // We create the floating object list lazily.
2829 if (!m_floatingObjects)
2830 createFloatingObjects();
2831
2832 // Applying the child's margin makes no sense in the case where the child was passed in.
2833 // since this margin was added already through the modification of the |logicalLeftOffset| variable
2834 // above. |logicalLeftOffset| will equal the margin in this case, so it's already been taken
2835 // into account. Only apply this code if prev is the parent, since otherwise the left margin
2836 // will get applied twice.
2837 LayoutSize offset = isHorizontalWritingMode()
2838 ? LayoutSize(logicalLeftOffset - (prev != container ? prev->marginLeft() : 0_lu), logicalTopOffset)
2839 : LayoutSize(logicalTopOffset, logicalLeftOffset - (prev != container ? prev->marginTop() : 0_lu));
2840
2841 m_floatingObjects->add(floatingObject.copyToNewContainer(offset));
2842 }
2843 }
2844 }
2845}
2846
2847void RenderBlockFlow::markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout(RenderBox* floatToRemove, bool inLayout)
2848{
2849 if (!everHadLayout() && !containsFloats())
2850 return;
2851
2852 MarkingBehavior markParents = inLayout ? MarkOnlyThis : MarkContainingBlockChain;
2853 setChildNeedsLayout(markParents);
2854
2855 if (floatToRemove)
2856 removeFloatingObject(*floatToRemove);
2857 else if (childrenInline())
2858 return;
2859
2860 // Iterate over our block children and mark them as needed.
2861 for (auto& block : childrenOfType<RenderBlock>(*this)) {
2862 if (!floatToRemove && block.isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
2863 continue;
2864 if (!is<RenderBlockFlow>(block)) {
2865 if (block.shrinkToAvoidFloats() && block.everHadLayout())
2866 block.setChildNeedsLayout(markParents);
2867 continue;
2868 }
2869 auto& blockFlow = downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(block);
2870 if ((floatToRemove ? blockFlow.containsFloat(*floatToRemove) : blockFlow.containsFloats()) || blockFlow.shrinkToAvoidFloats())
2871 blockFlow.markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout(floatToRemove, inLayout);
2872 }
2873}
2874
2875void RenderBlockFlow::markSiblingsWithFloatsForLayout(RenderBox* floatToRemove)
2876{
2877 if (!m_floatingObjects)
2878 return;
2879
2880 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_floatingObjects->set();
2881 auto end = floatingObjectSet.end();
2882
2883 for (RenderObject* next = nextSibling(); next; next = next->nextSibling()) {
2884 if (!is<RenderBlockFlow>(*next) || next->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
2885 continue;
2886
2887 RenderBlockFlow& nextBlock = downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*next);
2888 for (auto it = floatingObjectSet.begin(); it != end; ++it) {
2889 RenderBox& floatingBox = (*it)->renderer();
2890 if (floatToRemove && &floatingBox != floatToRemove)
2891 continue;
2892 if (nextBlock.containsFloat(floatingBox))
2893 nextBlock.markAllDescendantsWithFloatsForLayout(&floatingBox);
2894 }
2895 }
2896}
2897
2898LayoutPoint RenderBlockFlow::flipFloatForWritingModeForChild(const FloatingObject& child, const LayoutPoint& point) const
2899{
2900 if (!style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode())
2901 return point;
2902
2903 // This is similar to RenderBox::flipForWritingModeForChild. We have to subtract out our left/top offsets twice, since
2904 // it's going to get added back in. We hide this complication here so that the calling code looks normal for the unflipped
2905 // case.
2906 if (isHorizontalWritingMode())
2907 return LayoutPoint(point.x(), point.y() + height() - child.renderer().height() - 2 * child.locationOffsetOfBorderBox().height());
2908 return LayoutPoint(point.x() + width() - child.renderer().width() - 2 * child.locationOffsetOfBorderBox().width(), point.y());
2909}
2910
2911LayoutUnit RenderBlockFlow::getClearDelta(RenderBox& child, LayoutUnit logicalTop)
2912{
2913 // There is no need to compute clearance if we have no floats.
2914 if (!containsFloats())
2915 return 0;
2916
2917 // At least one float is present. We need to perform the clearance computation.
2918 UsedClear usedClear = RenderStyle::usedClear(child);
2919 bool clearSet = usedClear != UsedClear::None;
2920 LayoutUnit logicalBottom;
2921 switch (usedClear) {
2922 case UsedClear::None:
2923 break;
2924 case UsedClear::Left:
2925 logicalBottom = lowestFloatLogicalBottom(FloatingObject::FloatLeft);
2926 break;
2927 case UsedClear::Right:
2928 logicalBottom = lowestFloatLogicalBottom(FloatingObject::FloatRight);
2929 break;
2930 case UsedClear::Both:
2931 logicalBottom = lowestFloatLogicalBottom();
2932 break;
2933 }
2934
2935 // We also clear floats if we are too big to sit on the same line as a float (and wish to avoid floats by default).
2936 LayoutUnit result = clearSet ? std::max<LayoutUnit>(0, logicalBottom - logicalTop) : 0_lu;
2937 if (!result && child.avoidsFloats()) {
2938 LayoutUnit newLogicalTop = logicalTop;
2939 while (true) {
2940 LayoutUnit availableLogicalWidthAtNewLogicalTopOffset = availableLogicalWidthForLine(newLogicalTop, DoNotIndentText, logicalHeightForChild(child));
2941 if (availableLogicalWidthAtNewLogicalTopOffset == availableLogicalWidthForContent(newLogicalTop))
2942 return newLogicalTop - logicalTop;
2943
2944 RenderFragmentContainer* fragment = fragmentAtBlockOffset(logicalTopForChild(child));
2945 LayoutRect borderBox = child.borderBoxRectInFragment(fragment, DoNotCacheRenderBoxFragmentInfo);
2946 LayoutUnit childLogicalWidthAtOldLogicalTopOffset = isHorizontalWritingMode() ? borderBox.width() : borderBox.height();
2947
2948 // FIXME: None of this is right for perpendicular writing-mode children.
2949 LayoutUnit childOldLogicalWidth = child.logicalWidth();
2950 LayoutUnit childOldMarginLeft = child.marginLeft();
2951 LayoutUnit childOldMarginRight = child.marginRight();
2952 LayoutUnit childOldLogicalTop = child.logicalTop();
2953
2954 child.setLogicalTop(newLogicalTop);
2955 child.updateLogicalWidth();
2956 fragment = fragmentAtBlockOffset(logicalTopForChild(child));
2957 borderBox = child.borderBoxRectInFragment(fragment, DoNotCacheRenderBoxFragmentInfo);
2958 LayoutUnit childLogicalWidthAtNewLogicalTopOffset = isHorizontalWritingMode() ? borderBox.width() : borderBox.height();
2959
2960 child.setLogicalTop(childOldLogicalTop);
2961 child.setLogicalWidth(childOldLogicalWidth);
2962 child.setMarginLeft(childOldMarginLeft);
2963 child.setMarginRight(childOldMarginRight);
2964
2965 if (childLogicalWidthAtNewLogicalTopOffset <= availableLogicalWidthAtNewLogicalTopOffset) {
2966 // Even though we may not be moving, if the logical width did shrink because of the presence of new floats, then
2967 // we need to force a relayout as though we shifted. This happens because of the dynamic addition of overhanging floats
2968 // from previous siblings when negative margins exist on a child (see the addOverhangingFloats call at the end of collapseMargins).
2969 if (childLogicalWidthAtOldLogicalTopOffset != childLogicalWidthAtNewLogicalTopOffset)
2970 child.setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
2971 return newLogicalTop - logicalTop;
2972 }
2973
2974 newLogicalTop = nextFloatLogicalBottomBelowForBlock(newLogicalTop);
2975 ASSERT(newLogicalTop >= logicalTop);
2976 if (newLogicalTop < logicalTop)
2977 break;
2978 }
2979 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
2980 }
2981 return result;
2982}

2984bool RenderBlockFlow::hitTestFloats(const HitTestRequest& request, HitTestResult& result, const HitTestLocation& locationInContainer, const LayoutPoint& accumulatedOffset)
2985{
2986 if (!m_floatingObjects)
2987 return false;
2988
2989 LayoutPoint adjustedLocation = accumulatedOffset;
2990 if (is<RenderView>(*this))
2991 adjustedLocation += toLayoutSize(downcast<RenderView>(*this).frameView().scrollPosition());
2992
2993 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_floatingObjects->set();
2994 auto begin = floatingObjectSet.begin();
2995 for (auto it = floatingObjectSet.end(); it != begin;) {
2996 --it;
2997 const auto& floatingObject = *it->get();
2998 auto& renderer = floatingObject.renderer();
2999 if (floatingObject.shouldPaint()) {
3000 LayoutPoint childPoint = flipFloatForWritingModeForChild(floatingObject, adjustedLocation + floatingObject.translationOffsetToAncestor());
3001 if (renderer.hitTest(request, result, locationInContainer, childPoint)) {
3002 updateHitTestResult(result, locationInContainer.point() - toLayoutSize(childPoint));
3003 return true;
3004 }
3005 }
3006 }
3007
3008 return false;
3009}

3035
3036void RenderBlockFlow::adjustForBorderFit(LayoutUnit x, LayoutUnit& left, LayoutUnit& right) const
3037{
3038 if (style().visibility() != Visibility::Visible)
3039 return;
3040
3041 // We don't deal with relative positioning. Our assumption is that you shrink to fit the lines without accounting
3042 // for either overflow or translations via relative positioning.
3043 if (childrenInline()) {
3044 const_cast<RenderBlockFlow&>(*this).ensureLineBoxes();
3045
3046 for (auto* box = firstRootBox(); box; box = box->nextRootBox()) {
3047 if (box->firstChild())
3048 left = std::min(left, x + LayoutUnit(box->firstChild()->x()));
3049 if (box->lastChild())
3050 right = std::max(right, x + LayoutUnit(ceilf(box->lastChild()->logicalRight())));
3051 }
3052 } else {
3053 for (RenderBox* obj = firstChildBox(); obj; obj = obj->nextSiblingBox()) {
3054 if (!obj->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned()) {
3055 if (is<RenderBlockFlow>(*obj) && !obj->hasOverflowClip())
3056 downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*obj).adjustForBorderFit(x + obj->x(), left, right);
3057 else if (obj->style().visibility() == Visibility::Visible) {
3058 // We are a replaced element or some kind of non-block-flow object.
3059 left = std::min(left, x + obj->x());
3060 right = std::max(right, x + obj->x() + obj->width());
3061 }
3062 }
3063 }
3064 }
3065
3066 if (m_floatingObjects) {
3067 const FloatingObjectSet& floatingObjectSet = m_floatingObjects->set();
3068 auto end = floatingObjectSet.end();
3069 for (auto it = floatingObjectSet.begin(); it != end; ++it) {
3070 const auto& floatingObject = *it->get();
3071 if (floatingObject.paintsFloat()) {
3072 LayoutUnit floatLeft = floatingObject.translationOffsetToAncestor().width();
3073 LayoutUnit floatRight = floatLeft + floatingObject.renderer().width();
3074 left = std::min(left, floatLeft);
3075 right = std::max(right, floatRight);
3076 }
3077 }
3078 }
3079}
3080
3081void RenderBlockFlow::fitBorderToLinesIfNeeded()
3082{
3083 if (style().borderFit() == BorderFit::Border || hasOverridingLogicalWidth())
3084 return;
3085
3086 // Walk any normal flow lines to snugly fit.
3087 LayoutUnit left = LayoutUnit::max();
3088 LayoutUnit right = LayoutUnit::min();
3089 LayoutUnit oldWidth = contentWidth();
3090 adjustForBorderFit(0, left, right);
3091
3092 // Clamp to our existing edges. We can never grow. We only shrink.
3093 LayoutUnit leftEdge = borderLeft() + paddingLeft();
3094 LayoutUnit rightEdge = leftEdge + oldWidth;
3095 left = std::min(rightEdge, std::max(leftEdge, left));
3096 right = std::max(leftEdge, std::min(rightEdge, right));
3097
3098 LayoutUnit newContentWidth = right - left;
3099 if (newContentWidth == oldWidth)
3100 return;
3101
3102 setOverridingLogicalWidth(newContentWidth + borderAndPaddingLogicalWidth());
3103 layoutBlock(false);
3104 clearOverridingLogicalWidth();
3105}

3107void RenderBlockFlow::markLinesDirtyInBlockRange(LayoutUnit logicalTop, LayoutUnit logicalBottom, LegacyRootInlineBox* highest)
3108{
3109 if (logicalTop >= logicalBottom)
3110 return;
3111
3112 // Floats currently affect the choice of layout path.
3113#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
3114 if (modernLineLayout()) {
3115 invalidateLineLayoutPath();
3116 return;
3117 }
3118#endif
3119
3120 LegacyRootInlineBox* lowestDirtyLine = lastRootBox();
3121 LegacyRootInlineBox* afterLowest = lowestDirtyLine;
3122 while (lowestDirtyLine && lowestDirtyLine->lineBoxBottom() >= logicalBottom && logicalBottom < LayoutUnit::max()) {
3123 afterLowest = lowestDirtyLine;
3124 lowestDirtyLine = lowestDirtyLine->prevRootBox();
3125 }
3126
3127 while (afterLowest && afterLowest != highest && (afterLowest->lineBoxBottom() >= logicalTop || afterLowest->lineBoxBottom() < 0)) {
3128 afterLowest->markDirty();
3129 afterLowest = afterLowest->prevRootBox();
3130 }
3131}

3133std::optional<LayoutUnit> RenderBlockFlow::firstLineBaseline() const
3134{
3135 if (isWritingModeRoot() && !isRubyRun() && !isGridItem())
3136 return std::nullopt;
3137
3138 if (shouldApplyLayoutContainment(*this))
3139 return std::nullopt;
3140
3141 if (!childrenInline())
3142 return RenderBlock::firstLineBaseline();
3143
3144 if (!hasLines())
3145 return std::nullopt;
3146
3147#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
3148 if (modernLineLayout())
3149 return LayoutUnit { floorToInt(modernLineLayout()->firstLineBaseline()) };
3150#endif
3151
3152 ASSERT(firstRootBox());
3153 if (style().isFlippedLinesWritingMode())
3154 return LayoutUnit { firstRootBox()->logicalTop() + firstLineStyle().fontMetrics().descent(firstRootBox()->baselineType()) };
3155 return LayoutUnit { firstRootBox()->logicalTop() + firstLineStyle().fontMetrics().ascent(firstRootBox()->baselineType()) };
3156}
3157
3158std::optional<LayoutUnit> RenderBlockFlow::inlineBlockBaseline(LineDirectionMode lineDirection) const
3159{
3160 if (isWritingModeRoot() && !isRubyRun())
3161 return std::nullopt;
3162
3163 if (shouldApplyLayoutContainment(*this))
3164 return RenderBlock::inlineBlockBaseline(lineDirection);
3165
3166 if (style().display() == DisplayType::InlineBlock) {
3167 // The baseline of an 'inline-block' is the baseline of its last line box in the normal flow, unless it has either no in-flow line boxes or if its 'overflow'
3168 // property has a computed value other than 'visible'. see https://www.w3.org/TR/CSS22/visudet.html
3169 auto shouldSynthesizeBaseline = !style().isOverflowVisible() && !is<HTMLFormControlElement>(element());
3170 if (shouldSynthesizeBaseline)
3171 return std::nullopt;
3172 }
3173 // Note that here we only take the left and bottom into consideration. Our caller takes the right and top into consideration.
3174 float boxHeight = synthesizedBaselineFromBorderBox(*this, lineDirection) + (lineDirection == HorizontalLine ? m_marginBox.bottom() : m_marginBox.left());
3175 float lastBaseline = 0;
3176 if (!childrenInline()) {
3177 auto inlineBlockBaseline = RenderBlock::inlineBlockBaseline(lineDirection);
3178 if (!inlineBlockBaseline)
3179 return inlineBlockBaseline;
3180 lastBaseline = inlineBlockBaseline.value();
3181 } else {
3182 if (!hasLines()) {
3183 if (!hasLineIfEmpty())
3184 return std::nullopt;
3185 const auto& fontMetrics = firstLineStyle().fontMetrics();
3186 return LayoutUnit { LayoutUnit(fontMetrics.ascent()
3187 + (lineHeight(true, lineDirection, PositionOfInteriorLineBoxes) - fontMetrics.height()) / 2
3188 + (lineDirection == HorizontalLine ? borderTop() + paddingTop() : borderRight() + paddingRight())).toInt() };
3189 }
3190
3191 if (legacyLineLayout()) {
3192 bool isFirstLine = lastRootBox() == firstRootBox();
3193 const auto& style = isFirstLine ? firstLineStyle() : this->style();
3194 // LegacyInlineFlowBox::placeBoxesInBlockDirection will flip lines in case of verticalLR mode, so we can assume verticalRL for now.
3195 lastBaseline = style.fontMetrics().ascent(lastRootBox()->baselineType())
3196 + (style.isFlippedLinesWritingMode() ? logicalHeight() - lastRootBox()->logicalBottom() : lastRootBox()->logicalTop());
3197 }
3198#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
3199 else if (modernLineLayout())
3200 lastBaseline = floorToInt(modernLineLayout()->lastLineBaseline());
3201#endif
3202 }
3203 // According to the CSS spec http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/visudet.html, we shouldn't be performing this min, but should
3204 // instead be returning boxHeight directly. However, we feel that a min here is better behavior (and is consistent
3205 // enough with the spec to not cause tons of breakages).
3206 return LayoutUnit { style().overflowY() == Overflow::Visible ? lastBaseline : std::min(boxHeight, lastBaseline) };
3207}

3215
3216GapRects RenderBlockFlow::inlineSelectionGaps(RenderBlock& rootBlock, const LayoutPoint& rootBlockPhysicalPosition, const LayoutSize& offsetFromRootBlock,
3217 LayoutUnit& lastLogicalTop, LayoutUnit& lastLogicalLeft, LayoutUnit& lastLogicalRight, const LogicalSelectionOffsetCaches& cache, const PaintInfo* paintInfo)
3218{
3219 GapRects result;
3220
3221 bool containsStart = selectionState() == HighlightState::Start || selectionState() == HighlightState::Both;
3222
3223 if (!hasLines()) {
3224 if (containsStart) {
3225 // Update our lastLogicalTop to be the bottom of the block. <hr>s or empty blocks with height can trip this case.
3226 lastLogicalTop = blockDirectionOffset(rootBlock, offsetFromRootBlock) + logicalHeight();
3227 lastLogicalLeft = logicalLeftSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalHeight(), cache);
3228 lastLogicalRight = logicalRightSelectionOffset(rootBlock, logicalHeight(), cache);
3229 }
3230 return result;
3231 }
3232
3233 auto hasSelectedChildren = [&](const LegacyRootInlineBox& root) {
3234 for (auto* box = root.firstLeafDescendant(); box; box = box->nextLeafOnLine()) {
3235 if (!is<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*box)) {
3236 if (box->selectionState() != HighlightState::None)
3237 return true;
3238 continue;
3239 }
3240
3241 auto start = view().selection().startOffset();
3242 auto end = view().selection().endOffset();
3243
3244 auto& textBox = downcast<LegacyInlineTextBox>(*box);
3245 switch (textBox.renderer().selectionState()) {
3246 case RenderObject::HighlightState::None:
3247 continue;
3248 case RenderObject::HighlightState::Inside:
3249 return true;
3250 case RenderObject::HighlightState::Start:
3251 end = textBox.renderer().text().length();
3252 // to handle selection from end of text to end of line
3253 if (start && start == end)
3254 start = end - 1;
3255 break;
3256 case RenderObject::HighlightState::End:
3257 start = 0;
3258 break;
3259 case RenderObject::HighlightState::Both:
3260 break;
3261 }
3262 if (textBox.isSelectable(start, end))
3263 return true;
3264 }
3265 return false;
3266 };
3267
3268 LegacyRootInlineBox* lastSelectedLine = 0;
3269 LegacyRootInlineBox* curr;
3270 for (curr = firstRootBox(); curr && !hasSelectedChildren(*curr); curr = curr->nextRootBox()) { }
3271
3272 // Now paint the gaps for the lines.
3273 for (; curr && hasSelectedChildren(*curr); curr = curr->nextRootBox()) {
3274 LayoutUnit selTop = curr->selectionTopAdjustedForPrecedingBlock();
3275 LayoutUnit selHeight = curr->selectionHeightAdjustedForPrecedingBlock();
3276
3277 if (!containsStart && !lastSelectedLine &&
3278 selectionState() != HighlightState::Start && selectionState() != HighlightState::Both && !isRubyBase())
3279 result.uniteCenter(blockSelectionGap(rootBlock, rootBlockPhysicalPosition, offsetFromRootBlock, lastLogicalTop, lastLogicalLeft, lastLogicalRight, selTop, cache, paintInfo));
3280
3281 LayoutRect logicalRect { LayoutUnit(curr->logicalLeft()), selTop, LayoutUnit(curr->logicalWidth()), selTop + selHeight };
3282 logicalRect.move(isHorizontalWritingMode() ? offsetFromRootBlock : offsetFromRootBlock.transposedSize());
3283 LayoutRect physicalRect = rootBlock.logicalRectToPhysicalRect(rootBlockPhysicalPosition, logicalRect);
3284 if (!paintInfo || (isHorizontalWritingMode() && physicalRect.y() < paintInfo->rect.maxY() && physicalRect.maxY() > paintInfo->rect.y())
3285 || (!isHorizontalWritingMode() && physicalRect.x() < paintInfo->rect.maxX() && physicalRect.maxX() > paintInfo->rect.x()))
3286 result.unite(curr->lineSelectionGap(rootBlock, rootBlockPhysicalPosition, offsetFromRootBlock, selTop, selHeight, cache, paintInfo));
3287
3288 lastSelectedLine = curr;
3289 }
3290
3291 if (containsStart && !lastSelectedLine)
3292 // VisibleSelection must start just after our last line.
3293 lastSelectedLine = lastRootBox();
3294
3295 if (lastSelectedLine && selectionState() != HighlightState::End && selectionState() != HighlightState::Both) {
3296 // Update our lastY to be the bottom of the last selected line.
3297 lastLogicalTop = blockDirectionOffset(rootBlock, offsetFromRootBlock) + lastSelectedLine->selectionBottom();
3298 lastLogicalLeft = logicalLeftSelectionOffset(rootBlock, lastSelectedLine->selectionBottom(), cache);
3299 lastLogicalRight = logicalRightSelectionOffset(rootBlock, lastSelectedLine->selectionBottom(), cache);
3300 }
3301 return result;
3302}

3327
3328bool shouldIncludeLinesForParentLineCount(const RenderBlockFlow& blockFlow)
3329{

3406
3407RenderText* RenderBlockFlow::findClosestTextAtAbsolutePoint(const FloatPoint& point)
3408{
3409 // A light, non-recursive version of RenderBlock::positionForCoordinates that looks at
3410 // whether a point lies within the gaps between its root line boxes, to be called against
3411 // a node returned from elementAtPoint. We make the assumption that either the node or one
3412 // of its immediate children contains the root line boxes in question.
3413 // See <rdar://problem/6824650> for context.
3414
3415 RenderBlock* block = this;
3416
3417 FloatPoint localPoint = block->absoluteToLocal(point);
3418
3419 if (!block->childrenInline()) {
3420 // Look among our immediate children for an alternate box that contains the point.
3421 for (RenderBox* child = block->firstChildBox(); child; child = child->nextSiblingBox()) {
3422 if (!child->height() || child->style().visibility() != WebCore::Visibility::Visible || child->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
3423 continue;
3424 float top = child->y();
3425
3426 RenderBox* nextChild = child->nextSiblingBox();
3427 while (nextChild && nextChild->isFloatingOrOutOfFlowPositioned())
3428 nextChild = nextChild->nextSiblingBox();
3429 if (!nextChild) {
3430 if (localPoint.y() >= top) {
3431 block = downcast<RenderBlock>(child);
3432 break;
3433 }
3434 continue;
3435 }
3436
3437 float bottom = nextChild->y();
3438
3439 if (localPoint.y() >= top && localPoint.y() < bottom && is<RenderBlock>(*child)) {
3440 block = downcast<RenderBlock>(child);
3441 break;
3442 }
3443 }
3444
3445 if (!block->childrenInline())
3446 return nullptr;
3447
3448 localPoint = block->absoluteToLocal(point);
3449 }
3450
3451 RenderBlockFlow& blockFlow = downcast<RenderBlockFlow>(*block);
3452
3453 // Only check the gaps between the root line boxes. We deliberately ignore overflow because
3454 // experience has shown that hit tests on an exploded text node can fail when within the
3455 // overflow fragment.
3456 for (auto current = LayoutIntegration::firstLineFor(blockFlow), last = LayoutIntegration::lastLineFor(blockFlow); current && current != last; current.traverseNext()) {
3457 float currentBottom = current->y() + current->logicalHeight();
3458 if (localPoint.y() < currentBottom)
3459 return nullptr;
3460
3461 auto next = current.next();
3462 float nextTop = next->y();
3463 if (localPoint.y() < nextTop) {
3464 auto run = current.closestRunForLogicalLeftPosition(localPoint.x());
3465 if (run && is<RenderText>(run->renderer()))
3466 return const_cast<RenderText*>(&downcast<RenderText>(run->renderer()));
3467 }
3468 }
3469 return nullptr;
3470}

3472VisiblePosition RenderBlockFlow::positionForPointWithInlineChildren(const LayoutPoint& pointInLogicalContents, const RenderFragmentContainer* fragment)
3473{
3474 ASSERT(childrenInline());
3475
3476 auto firstLine = LayoutIntegration::firstLineFor(*this);
3477
3478 if (!firstLine)
3479 return createVisiblePosition(0, Affinity::Downstream);
3480
3481 bool linesAreFlipped = style().isFlippedLinesWritingMode();
3482 bool blocksAreFlipped = style().isFlippedBlocksWritingMode();
3483
3484 // look for the closest line box in the root box which is at the passed-in y coordinate
3485 LayoutIntegration::RunIterator closestRun;
3486 LayoutIntegration::LineIterator firstLineWithChildren;
3487 LayoutIntegration::LineIterator lastLineWithChildren;
3488 for (auto line = firstLine; line; line.traverseNext()) {
3489 if (fragment && line->legacyRootInlineBox() && line->legacyRootInlineBox()->containingFragment() != fragment)
3490 continue;
3491
3492 if (!line.firstRun())
3493 continue;
3494 if (!firstLineWithChildren)
3495 firstLineWithChildren = line;
3496
3497 if (!linesAreFlipped && line->legacyRootInlineBox() && line->legacyRootInlineBox()->isFirstAfterPageBreak()
3498 && (pointInLogicalContents.y() < line->lineBoxTop() || (blocksAreFlipped && pointInLogicalContents.y() == line->lineBoxTop())))
3499 break;
3500
3501 lastLineWithChildren = line;
3502
3503 // check if this root line box is located at this y coordinate
3504 if (pointInLogicalContents.y() < line->selectionBottom() || (blocksAreFlipped && pointInLogicalContents.y() == line->selectionBottom())) {
3505 if (linesAreFlipped) {
3506 auto nextLineWithChildren = line.next();
3507 while (nextLineWithChildren && !nextLineWithChildren.firstRun())
3508 nextLineWithChildren.traverseNext();
3509
3510 if (nextLineWithChildren && nextLineWithChildren->legacyRootInlineBox() && nextLineWithChildren->legacyRootInlineBox()->isFirstAfterPageBreak()
3511 && (pointInLogicalContents.y() > nextLineWithChildren->lineBoxTop() || (!blocksAreFlipped && pointInLogicalContents.y() == nextLineWithChildren->lineBoxTop())))
3512 continue;
3513 }
3514 closestRun = line.closestRunForLogicalLeftPosition(pointInLogicalContents.x());
3515 if (closestRun)
3516 break;
3517 }
3518 }
3519
3520 bool moveCaretToBoundary = frame().editor().behavior().shouldMoveCaretToHorizontalBoundaryWhenPastTopOrBottom();
3521
3522 if (!moveCaretToBoundary && !closestRun && lastLineWithChildren) {
3523 // y coordinate is below last root line box, pretend we hit it
3524 closestRun = lastLineWithChildren.closestRunForLogicalLeftPosition(pointInLogicalContents.x());
3525 }
3526
3527 if (closestRun) {
3528 if (moveCaretToBoundary) {
3529 LayoutUnit firstLineWithChildrenTop = std::min(firstLineWithChildren->selectionTopForHitTesting(), LayoutUnit(firstLineWithChildren->top()));
3530 if (pointInLogicalContents.y() < firstLineWithChildrenTop
3531 || (blocksAreFlipped && pointInLogicalContents.y() == firstLineWithChildrenTop)) {
3532 auto run = firstLineWithChildren.firstRun();
3533 if (run->isLineBreak()) {
3534 if (auto next = run.nextOnLineIgnoringLineBreak())
3535 run = next;
3536 }
3537 // y coordinate is above first root line box, so return the start of the first
3538 return positionForRun(*this, run, true);
3539 }
3540 }
3541
3542 // pass the box a top position that is inside it
3543 LayoutPoint point(pointInLogicalContents.x(), closestRun.line()->blockDirectionPointInLine());
3544 if (!isHorizontalWritingMode())
3545 point = point.transposedPoint();
3546 if (closestRun->renderer().isReplaced())
3547 return positionForPointRespectingEditingBoundaries(*this, const_cast<RenderBox&>(downcast<RenderBox>(closestRun->renderer())), point);
3548 return const_cast<RenderObject&>(closestRun->renderer()).positionForPoint(point, nullptr);
3549 }
3550
3551 if (lastLineWithChildren) {
3552 // We hit this case for Mac behavior when the Y coordinate is below the last box.
3553 ASSERT(moveCaretToBoundary);
3554 if (auto logicallyLastRun = lastLineWithChildren.logicalEndRunWithNode())
3555 return positionForRun(*this, logicallyLastRun, false);
3556 }
3557
3558 // Can't reach this. We have a root line box, but it has no kids.
3559 // FIXME: This should ASSERT_NOT_REACHED(), but clicking on placeholder text
3560 // seems to hit this code path.
3561 return createVisiblePosition(0, Affinity::Downstream);
3562}

3600
3601bool RenderBlockFlow::relayoutForPagination()
3602{
3603 if (!multiColumnFlow() || !multiColumnFlow()->shouldRelayoutForPagination())
3604 return false;
3605
3606 multiColumnFlow()->setNeedsHeightsRecalculation(false);
3607 multiColumnFlow()->setInBalancingPass(true); // Prevent re-entering this method (and recursion into layout).
3608
3609 bool needsRelayout;
3610 bool neededRelayout = false;
3611 bool firstPass = true;
3612 do {
3613 // Column heights may change here because of balancing. We may have to do multiple layout
3614 // passes, depending on how the contents is fitted to the changed column heights. In most
3615 // cases, laying out again twice or even just once will suffice. Sometimes we need more
3616 // passes than that, though, but the number of retries should not exceed the number of
3617 // columns, unless we have a bug.
3618 needsRelayout = false;
3619 for (RenderMultiColumnSet* multicolSet = multiColumnFlow()->firstMultiColumnSet(); multicolSet; multicolSet = multicolSet->nextSiblingMultiColumnSet()) {
3620 if (multicolSet->recalculateColumnHeight(firstPass))
3621 needsRelayout = true;
3622 if (needsRelayout) {
3623 // Once a column set gets a new column height, that column set and all successive column
3624 // sets need to be laid out over again, since their logical top will be affected by
3625 // this, and therefore their column heights may change as well, at least if the multicol
3626 // height is constrained.
3627 multicolSet->setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
3628 }
3629 }
3630 if (needsRelayout) {
3631 // Layout again. Column balancing resulted in a new height.
3632 neededRelayout = true;
3633 multiColumnFlow()->setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
3634 setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
3635 layoutBlock(false);
3636 }
3637 firstPass = false;
3638 } while (needsRelayout);
3639
3640 multiColumnFlow()->setInBalancingPass(false);
3641
3642 return neededRelayout;
3643}
