3686#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
3687void RenderBlockFlow::layoutModernLines(bool relayoutChildren, LayoutUnit& repaintLogicalTop, LayoutUnit& repaintLogicalBottom)
3688{
3689 bool needsUpdateReplacedDimensions = false;
3690
3691 if (!modernLineLayout()) {
3692 m_lineLayout = makeUnique<LayoutIntegration::LineLayout>(*this);
3693 needsUpdateReplacedDimensions = true;
3694 }
3695
3696 auto& layoutFormattingContextLineLayout = *this->modernLineLayout();
3697
3698 for (auto walker = InlineWalker(*this); !walker.atEnd(); walker.advance()) {
3699 auto& renderer = *walker.current();
3700 if (relayoutChildren)
3701 renderer.setNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
3702 if (!renderer.needsLayout() && !needsUpdateReplacedDimensions)
3703 continue;
3704
3705 if (is<RenderReplaced>(renderer)) {
3706 auto& replaced = downcast<RenderReplaced>(renderer);
3707 replaced.layoutIfNeeded();
3708 layoutFormattingContextLineLayout.updateReplacedDimensions(replaced);
3709 continue;
3710 }
3711 if (is<RenderBlock>(renderer)) {
3712 auto& block = downcast<RenderBlock>(renderer);
3713 block.layoutIfNeeded();
3714 ASSERT(block.style().display() == DisplayType::InlineBlock);
3715 layoutFormattingContextLineLayout.updateInlineBlockDimensions(block);
3716 continue;
3717 }
3718
3719 if (is<RenderLineBreak>(renderer)) {
3720 layoutFormattingContextLineLayout.updateLineBreakBoxDimensions(downcast<RenderLineBreak>(renderer));
3721 renderer.clearNeedsLayout();
3722 continue;
3723 }
3724
3725 if (is<RenderInline>(renderer)) {
3726 layoutFormattingContextLineLayout.updateInlineBoxDimensions(downcast<RenderInline>(renderer));
3727 renderer.clearNeedsLayout();
3728 continue;
3729 }
3730
3731 renderer.clearNeedsLayout();
3732 }
3733
3734 layoutFormattingContextLineLayout.layout();
3735
3736 if (view().frameView().layoutContext().layoutState()->isPaginated())
3737 layoutFormattingContextLineLayout.adjustForPagination();
3738
3739 auto contentHeight = [&] {
3740 if (!hasLines() && hasLineIfEmpty())
3741 return lineHeight(true, isHorizontalWritingMode() ? HorizontalLine : VerticalLine, PositionOfInteriorLineBoxes);
3742
3743 return layoutFormattingContextLineLayout.contentLogicalHeight();
3744 }();
3745 auto contentBoxTop = borderAndPaddingBefore();
3746 auto contentBoxBottom = contentBoxTop + contentHeight;
3747 auto borderBoxBottom = contentBoxBottom + borderAndPaddingAfter();
3748
3749 repaintLogicalTop = contentBoxTop;
3750 repaintLogicalBottom = borderBoxBottom;
3751 setLogicalHeight(borderBoxBottom);
3752}

3755void RenderBlockFlow::ensureLineBoxes()
3756{
3757 if (!childrenInline())
3758 return;
3759
3760 setLineLayoutPath(ForceLineBoxesPath);
3761
3762 if (legacyLineLayout() || !hasLineLayout())
3763 return;
3764
3765 bool needsToPaginateComplexLines = [&] {
3766#if ENABLE(LAYOUT_FORMATTING_CONTEXT)
3767 if (modernLineLayout() && modernLineLayout()->isPaginated())
3768 return true;
3769#endif
3770 return false;
3771 }();
3772
3773 m_lineLayout = makeUnique<LegacyLineLayout>(*this);
3774
3775 auto& legacyLineLayout = *this->legacyLineLayout();
3776
3777#if ASSERT_ENABLED
3778 LayoutUnit oldHeight = logicalHeight();
3779#endif
3780 bool didNeedLayout = needsLayout();
3781
3782 bool relayoutChildren = false;
3783 LayoutUnit repaintLogicalTop;
3784 LayoutUnit repaintLogicalBottom;
3785 if (needsToPaginateComplexLines) {
3786 PaginatedLayoutStateMaintainer state(*this);
3787 legacyLineLayout.layoutLineBoxes(relayoutChildren, repaintLogicalTop, repaintLogicalBottom);
3788 // This matches relayoutToAvoidWidows.
3789 if (shouldBreakAtLineToAvoidWidow())
3790 legacyLineLayout.layoutLineBoxes(relayoutChildren, repaintLogicalTop, repaintLogicalBottom);
3791 // FIXME: This is needed as long as simple and normal line layout produce different line breakings.
3792 repaint();
3793 } else
3794 legacyLineLayout.layoutLineBoxes(relayoutChildren, repaintLogicalTop, repaintLogicalBottom);
3795
3796 updateLogicalHeight();

3799 if (!didNeedLayout)
3800 clearNeedsLayout();
3801}

3893// For now, we auto size single lines of text the same as multiple lines.
3894// We've been experimenting with low values for single lines of text.
3895static inline float oneLineTextMultiplier(RenderObject& renderer, float specifiedSize)
3896{
3897 const float coefficient = renderer.settings().oneLineTextMultiplierCoefficient();
3898 return std::max((1.0f / log10f(specifiedSize) * coefficient), 1.0f);
3899}
3900
3901static inline float textMultiplier(RenderObject& renderer, float specifiedSize)
3902{
3903 const float coefficient = renderer.settings().multiLineTextMultiplierCoefficient();
3904 return std::max((1.0f / log10f(specifiedSize) * coefficient), 1.0f);
3905}
3906
3907void RenderBlockFlow::adjustComputedFontSizes(float size, float visibleWidth)
3908{
3909 LOG(TextAutosizing, "RenderBlockFlow %p adjustComputedFontSizes, size=%f visibleWidth=%f, width()=%f. Bailing: %d", this, size, visibleWidth, width().toFloat(), visibleWidth >= width());
3910
3911 // Don't do any work if the block is smaller than the visible area.
3912 if (visibleWidth >= width())
3913 return;
3914
3915 unsigned lineCount;
3916 if (m_lineCountForTextAutosizing == NOT_SET) {
3917 int count = lineCountForTextAutosizing();
3918 if (!count)
3919 lineCount = NO_LINE;
3920 else if (count == 1)
3921 lineCount = ONE_LINE;
3922 else
3923 lineCount = MULTI_LINE;
3924 } else
3925 lineCount = m_lineCountForTextAutosizing;
3926
3927 ASSERT(lineCount != NOT_SET);
3928 if (lineCount == NO_LINE)
3929 return;
3930
3931 float actualWidth = m_widthForTextAutosizing != -1 ? static_cast<float>(m_widthForTextAutosizing) : static_cast<float>(width());
3932 float scale = visibleWidth / actualWidth;
3933 float minFontSize = roundf(size / scale);
3934
3935 for (auto* descendant = RenderObjectTraversal::firstChild(*this); descendant; ) {
3936 if (!isNonBlocksOrNonFixedHeightListItems(*descendant)) {
3937 descendant = RenderObjectTraversal::nextSkippingChildren(*descendant, this);
3938 continue;
3939 }
3940 if (!isVisibleRenderText(*descendant) || !resizeTextPermitted(*descendant)) {
3941 descendant = RenderObjectTraversal::next(*descendant, this);
3942 continue;
3943 }
3944
3945 auto& text = downcast<RenderText>(*descendant);
3946 auto& oldStyle = text.style();
3947 auto& fontDescription = oldStyle.fontDescription();
3948 float specifiedSize = fontDescription.specifiedSize();
3949 float scaledSize = roundf(specifiedSize * scale);
3950 if (scaledSize > 0 && scaledSize < minFontSize) {
3951 // Record the width of the block and the line count the first time we resize text and use it from then on for text resizing.
3952 // This makes text resizing consistent even if the block's width or line count changes (which can be caused by text resizing itself 5159915).
3953 if (m_lineCountForTextAutosizing == NOT_SET)
3954 m_lineCountForTextAutosizing = lineCount;
3955 if (m_widthForTextAutosizing == -1)
3956 m_widthForTextAutosizing = actualWidth;
3957
3958 float lineTextMultiplier = lineCount == ONE_LINE ? oneLineTextMultiplier(text, specifiedSize) : textMultiplier(text, specifiedSize);
3959 float candidateNewSize = roundf(std::min(minFontSize, specifiedSize * lineTextMultiplier));
3960
3961 if (candidateNewSize > specifiedSize && candidateNewSize != fontDescription.computedSize() && text.textNode() && oldStyle.textSizeAdjust().isAuto())
3962 document().textAutoSizing().addTextNode(*text.textNode(), candidateNewSize);
3963 }
3964
3965 descendant = RenderObjectTraversal::nextSkippingChildren(text, this);
3966 }
3967}
3968
3969#endif // ENABLE(TEXT_AUTOSIZING)
3970
3971void RenderBlockFlow::layoutExcludedChildren(bool relayoutChildren)
3972{
3973 RenderBlock::layoutExcludedChildren(relayoutChildren);
3974
3975 auto* fragmentedFlow = multiColumnFlow();
3976 if (!fragmentedFlow)
3977 return;
3978
3979 fragmentedFlow->setIsExcludedFromNormalLayout(true);
3980
3981 setLogicalTopForChild(*fragmentedFlow, borderAndPaddingBefore());
3982
3983 if (relayoutChildren)
3984 fragmentedFlow->setChildNeedsLayout(MarkOnlyThis);
3985
3986 if (fragmentedFlow->needsLayout()) {
3987 for (RenderMultiColumnSet* columnSet = fragmentedFlow->firstMultiColumnSet(); columnSet; columnSet = columnSet->nextSiblingMultiColumnSet())
3988 columnSet->prepareForLayout(!fragmentedFlow->inBalancingPass());
3989
3990 fragmentedFlow->invalidateFragments(MarkOnlyThis);
3991 fragmentedFlow->setNeedsHeightsRecalculation(true);
3992 fragmentedFlow->layout();
3993 } else {
3994 // At the end of multicol layout, relayoutForPagination() is called unconditionally, but if
3995 // no children are to be laid out (e.g. fixed width with layout already being up-to-date),
3996 // we want to prevent it from doing any work, so that the column balancing machinery doesn't
3997 // kick in and trigger additional unnecessary layout passes. Actually, it's not just a good
3998 // idea in general to not waste time on balancing content that hasn't been re-laid out; we
3999 // are actually required to guarantee this. The calculation of implicit breaks needs to be
4000 // preceded by a proper layout pass, since it's layout that sets up content runs, and the
4001 // runs get deleted right after every pass.
4002 fragmentedFlow->setNeedsHeightsRecalculation(false);
4003 }
4004 determineLogicalLeftPositionForChild(*fragmentedFlow);
4005}
4006
4007void RenderBlockFlow::checkForPaginationLogicalHeightChange(bool& relayoutChildren, LayoutUnit& pageLogicalHeight, bool& pageLogicalHeightChanged)
4008{
4009 // If we don't use columns or flow threads, then bail.
4010 if (!isRenderFragmentedFlow() && !multiColumnFlow())
4011 return;
4012
4013 // We don't actually update any of the variables. We just subclassed to adjust our column height.
4014 if (RenderMultiColumnFlow* fragmentedFlow = multiColumnFlow()) {
4015 LayoutUnit newColumnHeight;
4016 if (hasDefiniteLogicalHeight() || view().frameView().pagination().mode != Pagination::Unpaginated) {
4017 auto computedValues = computeLogicalHeight(0_lu, logicalTop());
4018 newColumnHeight = std::max<LayoutUnit>(computedValues.m_extent - borderAndPaddingLogicalHeight() - scrollbarLogicalHeight(), 0);
4019 if (fragmentedFlow->columnHeightAvailable() != newColumnHeight)
4020 relayoutChildren = true;
4021 }
4022 fragmentedFlow->setColumnHeightAvailable(newColumnHeight);
4023 } else if (is<RenderFragmentedFlow>(*this)) {
4024 RenderFragmentedFlow& fragmentedFlow = downcast<RenderFragmentedFlow>(*this);
4025
4026 // FIXME: This is a hack to always make sure we have a page logical height, if said height
4027 // is known. The page logical height thing in RenderLayoutState is meaningless for flow
4028 // thread-based pagination (page height isn't necessarily uniform throughout the flow
4029 // thread), but as long as it is used universally as a means to determine whether page
4030 // height is known or not, we need this. Page height is unknown when column balancing is
4031 // enabled and flow thread height is still unknown (i.e. during the first layout pass). When
4032 // it's unknown, we need to prevent the pagination code from assuming page breaks everywhere
4033 // and thereby eating every top margin. It should be trivial to clean up and get rid of this
4034 // hack once the old multicol implementation is gone (see also RenderView::pushLayoutStateForPagination).
4035 pageLogicalHeight = fragmentedFlow.isPageLogicalHeightKnown() ? 1_lu : 0_lu;
4036
4037 pageLogicalHeightChanged = fragmentedFlow.pageLogicalSizeChanged();
4038 }

4119struct InlineMinMaxIterator {
4120/* InlineMinMaxIterator is a class that will iterate over all render objects that contribute to
4121 inline min/max width calculations. Note the following about the way it walks:
4122 (1) Positioned content is skipped (since it does not contribute to min/max width of a block)
4123 (2) We do not drill into the children of floats or replaced elements, since you can't break
4124 in the middle of such an element.
4125 (3) Inline flows (e.g., <a>, <span>, <i>) are walked twice, since each side can have
4126 distinct borders/margin/padding that contribute to the min/max width.
4127*/
4128 const RenderBlockFlow& parent;
4129 RenderObject* current;
4130 bool endOfInline;
4131 bool initial;
4132
4133 InlineMinMaxIterator(const RenderBlockFlow& p)
4134 : parent(p)
4135 , current(nullptr)
4136 , endOfInline(false)
4137 , initial(true)
4138 { }
4139
4140 RenderObject* next();
4141};
4142
4143RenderObject* InlineMinMaxIterator::next()
4144{
4145 RenderObject* result = nullptr;
4146 bool oldEndOfInline = endOfInline;
4147 endOfInline = false;
4148 do {
4149 if (!oldEndOfInline && (current && !current->isFloating() && !current->isReplaced() && !current->isOutOfFlowPositioned()))
4150 result = current->firstChildSlow();
4151 else if (initial) {
4152 result = parent.firstChild();
4153 initial = false;
4154 }
4155
4156 if (!result) {
4157 // We hit the end of our inline. (It was empty, e.g., <span></span>.)
4158 if (!oldEndOfInline && current && current->isRenderInline()) {
4159 result = current;
4160 endOfInline = true;
4161 break;
4162 }
4163
4164 while (current && current != &parent) {
4165 result = current->nextSibling();
4166 if (result)
4167 break;
4168 current = current->parent();
4169 if (current && current != &parent && current->isRenderInline()) {
4170 result = current;
4171 endOfInline = true;
4172 break;
4173 }
4174 }
4175 }
4176
4177 if (!result)
4178 break;
4179
4180 if (!result->isOutOfFlowPositioned() && (result->isTextOrLineBreak() || result->isFloating() || result->isReplaced() || result->isRenderInline()))
4181 break;
4182
4183 current = result;
4184 result = nullptr;
4185 } while (current || current == &parent);
4186 // Update our position.
4187 current = result;
4188 return result;
4189}

4191static LayoutUnit getBPMWidth(LayoutUnit childValue, Length cssUnit)
4192{
4193 if (cssUnit.type() != LengthType::Auto)
4194 return (cssUnit.isFixed() ? LayoutUnit(cssUnit.value()) : childValue);
4195 return 0;
4196}

4198static LayoutUnit getBorderPaddingMargin(const RenderBoxModelObject& child, bool endOfInline)
4199{
4200 const RenderStyle& childStyle = child.style();
4201 if (endOfInline) {
4202 return getBPMWidth(child.marginEnd(), childStyle.marginEnd()) +
4203 getBPMWidth(child.paddingEnd(), childStyle.paddingEnd()) +
4204 child.borderEnd();
4205 }
4206 return getBPMWidth(child.marginStart(), childStyle.marginStart()) +
4207 getBPMWidth(child.paddingStart(), childStyle.paddingStart()) +
4208 child.borderStart();
4209}

4211static inline void stripTrailingSpace(float& inlineMax, float& inlineMin, RenderObject* trailingSpaceChild)
4212{
4213 if (is<RenderText>(trailingSpaceChild)) {
4214 // Collapse away the trailing space at the end of a block.
4215 RenderText& renderText = downcast<RenderText>(*trailingSpaceChild);
4216 const UChar space = ' ';
4217 const FontCascade& font = renderText.style().fontCascade(); // FIXME: This ignores first-line.
4218 float spaceWidth = font.width(RenderBlock::constructTextRun(&space, 1, renderText.style()));
4219 inlineMax -= spaceWidth + font.wordSpacing();
4220 if (inlineMin > inlineMax)
4221 inlineMin = inlineMax;
4222 }
4223}

4225static inline LayoutUnit preferredWidth(LayoutUnit preferredWidth, float result)
4226{
4227 return std::max(preferredWidth, LayoutUnit::fromFloatCeil(result));
4228}
4229
4230void RenderBlockFlow::computeInlinePreferredLogicalWidths(LayoutUnit& minLogicalWidth, LayoutUnit& maxLogicalWidth) const
4231{
4232 float inlineMax = 0;
4233 float inlineMin = 0;
4234
4235 const RenderStyle& styleToUse = style();
4236 // If we are at the start of a line, we want to ignore all white-space.
4237 // Also strip spaces if we previously had text that ended in a trailing space.
4238 bool stripFrontSpaces = true;
4239 RenderObject* trailingSpaceChild = nullptr;
4240
4241 // Firefox and Opera will allow a table cell to grow to fit an image inside it under
4242 // very specific cirucumstances (in order to match common WinIE renderings).
4243 // Not supporting the quirk has caused us to mis-render some real sites. (See Bugzilla 10517.)
4244 bool allowImagesToBreak = !document().inQuirksMode() || !isTableCell() || !styleToUse.logicalWidth().isIntrinsicOrAuto();
4245
4246 bool oldAutoWrap = styleToUse.autoWrap();
4247
4248 InlineMinMaxIterator childIterator(*this);
4249
4250 // Only gets added to the max preffered width once.
4251 bool addedTextIndent = false;
4252 // Signals the text indent was more negative than the min preferred width
4253 bool hasRemainingNegativeTextIndent = false;
4254
4255 auto textIndent = LayoutUnit { };
4256 if (styleToUse.textIndent().isFixed())
4257 textIndent = LayoutUnit { styleToUse.textIndent().value() };
4258 else if (auto* containingBlock = this->containingBlock(); containingBlock && containingBlock->style().logicalWidth().isFixed()) {
4259 // At this point of the shrink-to-fit computatation, we don't have a used value for the containing block width
4260 // (that's exactly to what we try to contribute here) unless the computed value is fixed.
4261 textIndent = minimumValueForLength(styleToUse.textIndent(), containingBlock->style().logicalWidth().value());
4262 }
4263 RenderObject* previousFloat = 0;
4264 bool isPrevChildInlineFlow = false;
4265 bool shouldBreakLineAfterText = false;
4266 bool canHangPunctuationAtStart = styleToUse.hangingPunctuation().contains(HangingPunctuation::First);
4267 bool canHangPunctuationAtEnd = styleToUse.hangingPunctuation().contains(HangingPunctuation::Last);
4268 RenderText* lastText = nullptr;
4269
4270 bool addedStartPunctuationHang = false;
4271
4272 while (RenderObject* child = childIterator.next()) {
4273 bool autoWrap = child->isReplaced() ? child->parent()->style().autoWrap() :
4274 child->style().autoWrap();
4275 if (!child->isBR()) {
4276 // Step One: determine whether or not we need to terminate our current line.
4277 // Each discrete chunk can become the new min-width, if it is the widest chunk
4278 // seen so far, and it can also become the max-width.
4279
4280 // Children fall into three categories:
4281 // (1) An inline flow object. These objects always have a min/max of 0,
4282 // and are included in the iteration solely so that their margins can
4283 // be added in.
4284 //
4285 // (2) An inline non-text non-flow object, e.g., an inline replaced element.
4286 // These objects can always be on a line by themselves, so in this situation
4287 // we need to break the current line, and then add in our own margins and min/max
4288 // width on its own line, and then terminate the line.
4289 //
4290 // (3) A text object. Text runs can have breakable characters at the start,
4291 // the middle or the end. They may also lose whitespace off the front if
4292 // we're already ignoring whitespace. In order to compute accurate min-width
4293 // information, we need three pieces of information.
4294 // (a) the min-width of the first non-breakable run. Should be 0 if the text string
4295 // starts with whitespace.
4296 // (b) the min-width of the last non-breakable run. Should be 0 if the text string
4297 // ends with whitespace.
4298 // (c) the min/max width of the string (trimmed for whitespace).
4299 //
4300 // If the text string starts with whitespace, then we need to terminate our current line
4301 // (unless we're already in a whitespace stripping mode.
4302 //
4303 // If the text string has a breakable character in the middle, but didn't start
4304 // with whitespace, then we add the width of the first non-breakable run and
4305 // then end the current line. We then need to use the intermediate min/max width
4306 // values (if any of them are larger than our current min/max). We then look at
4307 // the width of the last non-breakable run and use that to start a new line
4308 // (unless we end in whitespace).
4309 const RenderStyle& childStyle = child->style();
4310 float childMin = 0;
4311 float childMax = 0;
4312
4313 if (!child->isText()) {
4314 if (child->isLineBreakOpportunity()) {
4315 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, inlineMin);
4316 inlineMin = 0;
4317 continue;
4318 }
4319 // Case (1) and (2). Inline replaced and inline flow elements.
4320 if (is<RenderInline>(*child)) {
4321 // Add in padding/border/margin from the appropriate side of
4322 // the element.
4323 float bpm = getBorderPaddingMargin(downcast<RenderInline>(*child), childIterator.endOfInline);
4324 childMin += bpm;
4325 childMax += bpm;
4326
4327 inlineMin += childMin;
4328 inlineMax += childMax;
4329
4330 child->setPreferredLogicalWidthsDirty(false);
4331 } else {
4332 // Inline replaced elts add in their margins to their min/max values.
4333 if (!child->isFloating())
4334 lastText = nullptr;
4335 LayoutUnit margins;
4336 Length startMargin = childStyle.marginStart();
4337 Length endMargin = childStyle.marginEnd();
4338 if (startMargin.isFixed())
4339 margins += LayoutUnit::fromFloatCeil(startMargin.value());
4340 if (endMargin.isFixed())
4341 margins += LayoutUnit::fromFloatCeil(endMargin.value());
4342 childMin += margins.ceilToFloat();
4343 childMax += margins.ceilToFloat();
4344 }
4345 }
4346
4347 if (!is<RenderInline>(*child) && !is<RenderText>(*child)) {
4348 // Case (2). Inline replaced elements and floats.
4349 // Terminate the current line as far as minwidth is concerned.
4350 LayoutUnit childMinPreferredLogicalWidth, childMaxPreferredLogicalWidth;
4351 computeChildPreferredLogicalWidths(*child, childMinPreferredLogicalWidth, childMaxPreferredLogicalWidth);
4352 childMin += childMinPreferredLogicalWidth.ceilToFloat();
4353 childMax += childMaxPreferredLogicalWidth.ceilToFloat();
4354
4355 bool clearPreviousFloat = false;
4356 if (child->isFloating()) {
4357 auto childClearValue = RenderStyle::usedClear(*child);
4358 if (previousFloat) {
4359 auto previousFloatValue = RenderStyle::usedFloat(*previousFloat);
4360 clearPreviousFloat =
4361 (previousFloatValue == UsedFloat::Left && (childClearValue == UsedClear::Left || childClearValue == UsedClear::Both))
4362 || (previousFloatValue == UsedFloat::Right && (childClearValue == UsedClear::Right || childClearValue == UsedClear::Both));
4363 }
4364 previousFloat = child;
4365 }
4366
4367 bool canBreakReplacedElement = !child->isImage() || allowImagesToBreak;
4368 if (((canBreakReplacedElement && (autoWrap || oldAutoWrap) && (!isPrevChildInlineFlow || shouldBreakLineAfterText)) || clearPreviousFloat)) {
4369 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, inlineMin);
4370 inlineMin = 0;
4371 }
4372
4373 // If we're supposed to clear the previous float, then terminate maxwidth as well.
4374 if (clearPreviousFloat) {
4375 maxLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(maxLogicalWidth, inlineMax);
4376 inlineMax = 0;
4377 }
4378
4379 // Add in text-indent. This is added in only once.
4380 if (!addedTextIndent && !child->isFloating()) {
4381 LayoutUnit ceiledIndent { textIndent.ceilToFloat() };
4382 childMin += ceiledIndent;
4383 childMax += ceiledIndent;
4384
4385 if (childMin < 0)
4386 textIndent = LayoutUnit::fromFloatCeil(childMin);
4387 else
4388 addedTextIndent = true;
4389 }
4390
4391 if (canHangPunctuationAtStart && !addedStartPunctuationHang && !child->isFloating())
4392 addedStartPunctuationHang = true;
4393
4394 // Add our width to the max.
4395 inlineMax += std::max<float>(0, childMax);
4396
4397 if ((!autoWrap || !canBreakReplacedElement || (isPrevChildInlineFlow && !shouldBreakLineAfterText))) {
4398 if (child->isFloating())
4399 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, childMin);
4400 else
4401 inlineMin += childMin;
4402 } else {
4403 // Now check our line.
4404 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, childMin);
4405
4406 // Now start a new line.
4407 inlineMin = 0;
4408 }
4409
4410 if (autoWrap && canBreakReplacedElement && isPrevChildInlineFlow) {
4411 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, inlineMin);
4412 inlineMin = 0;
4413 }
4414
4415 // We are no longer stripping whitespace at the start of a line.
4416 if (!child->isFloating()) {
4417 stripFrontSpaces = false;
4418 trailingSpaceChild = nullptr;
4419 lastText = nullptr;
4420 }
4421 } else if (is<RenderText>(*child)) {
4422 // Case (3). Text.
4423 RenderText& renderText = downcast<RenderText>(*child);
4424
4425 if (renderText.style().hasTextCombine() && renderText.isCombineText())
4426 downcast<RenderCombineText>(renderText).combineTextIfNeeded();
4427
4428 // Determine if we have a breakable character. Pass in
4429 // whether or not we should ignore any spaces at the front
4430 // of the string. If those are going to be stripped out,
4431 // then they shouldn't be considered in the breakable char
4432 // check.
4433 bool strippingBeginWS = stripFrontSpaces;
4434 auto widths = renderText.trimmedPreferredWidths(inlineMax, stripFrontSpaces);
4435
4436 childMin = widths.min;
4437 childMax = widths.max;
4438
4439 // This text object will not be rendered, but it may still provide a breaking opportunity.
4440 if (!widths.hasBreak && !childMax) {
4441 if (autoWrap && (widths.beginWS || widths.endWS)) {
4442 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, inlineMin);
4443 inlineMin = 0;
4444 }
4445 continue;
4446 }
4447
4448 lastText = &renderText;
4449
4450 if (stripFrontSpaces)
4451 trailingSpaceChild = child;
4452 else
4453 trailingSpaceChild = 0;
4454
4455 // Add in text-indent. This is added in only once.
4456 float ti = 0;
4457 if (!addedTextIndent || hasRemainingNegativeTextIndent) {
4458 ti = textIndent.ceilToFloat();
4459 childMin += ti;
4460 widths.beginMin += ti;
4461
4462 // It the text indent negative and larger than the child minimum, we re-use the remainder
4463 // in future minimum calculations, but using the negative value again on the maximum
4464 // will lead to under-counting the max pref width.
4465 if (!addedTextIndent) {
4466 childMax += ti;
4467 widths.beginMax += ti;
4468 addedTextIndent = true;
4469 }
4470
4471 if (childMin < 0) {
4472 textIndent = childMin;
4473 hasRemainingNegativeTextIndent = true;
4474 }
4475 }
4476
4477 // See if we have a hanging punctuation situation at the start.
4478 if (canHangPunctuationAtStart && !addedStartPunctuationHang) {
4479 unsigned startIndex = strippingBeginWS ? renderText.firstCharacterIndexStrippingSpaces() : 0;
4480 float hangStartWidth = renderText.hangablePunctuationStartWidth(startIndex);
4481 childMin -= hangStartWidth;
4482 widths.beginMin -= hangStartWidth;
4483 childMax -= hangStartWidth;
4484 widths.beginMax -= hangStartWidth;
4485 addedStartPunctuationHang = true;
4486 }
4487
4488 // If we have no breakable characters at all,
4489 // then this is the easy case. We add ourselves to the current
4490 // min and max and continue.
4491 if (!widths.hasBreakableChar)
4492 inlineMin += childMin;
4493 else {
4494 // We have a breakable character. Now we need to know if
4495 // we start and end with whitespace.
4496 if (widths.beginWS) {
4497 // End the current line.
4498 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, inlineMin);
4499 } else {
4500 inlineMin += widths.beginMin;
4501 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, inlineMin);
4502 childMin -= ti;
4503 }
4504
4505 inlineMin = childMin;
4506
4507 if (widths.endWS) {
4508 // We end in whitespace, which means we can end our current line.
4509 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, inlineMin);
4510 inlineMin = 0;
4511 shouldBreakLineAfterText = false;
4512 } else {
4513 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, inlineMin);
4514 inlineMin = widths.endMin;
4515 shouldBreakLineAfterText = true;
4516 }
4517 }
4518
4519 if (widths.hasBreak) {
4520 inlineMax += widths.beginMax;
4521 maxLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(maxLogicalWidth, inlineMax);
4522 maxLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(maxLogicalWidth, childMax);
4523 inlineMax = widths.endMax;
4524 addedTextIndent = true;
4525 addedStartPunctuationHang = true;
4526 } else
4527 inlineMax += std::max<float>(0, childMax);
4528 }
4529
4530 // Ignore spaces after a list marker.
4531 if (child->isListMarker())
4532 stripFrontSpaces = true;
4533 } else {
4534 if (styleToUse.collapseWhiteSpace())
4535 stripTrailingSpace(inlineMax, inlineMin, trailingSpaceChild);
4536 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, inlineMin);
4537 maxLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(maxLogicalWidth, inlineMax);
4538 inlineMin = inlineMax = 0;
4539 stripFrontSpaces = true;
4540 trailingSpaceChild = 0;
4541 addedTextIndent = true;
4542 addedStartPunctuationHang = true;
4543 }
4544
4545 if (!child->isText() && child->isRenderInline())
4546 isPrevChildInlineFlow = true;
4547 else
4548 isPrevChildInlineFlow = false;
4549
4550 oldAutoWrap = autoWrap;
4551 }
4552
4553 if (styleToUse.collapseWhiteSpace())
4554 stripTrailingSpace(inlineMax, inlineMin, trailingSpaceChild);
4555
4556 if (canHangPunctuationAtEnd && lastText && lastText->text().length() > 0) {
4557 unsigned endIndex = trailingSpaceChild == lastText ? lastText->lastCharacterIndexStrippingSpaces() : lastText->text().length() - 1;
4558 float endHangWidth = lastText->hangablePunctuationEndWidth(endIndex);
4559 inlineMin -= endHangWidth;
4560 inlineMax -= endHangWidth;
4561 }
4562
4563 minLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(minLogicalWidth, inlineMin);
4564 maxLogicalWidth = preferredWidth(maxLogicalWidth, inlineMax);
4565}
